column8: text

While I was sad to see Bibo close at this location, I've been a fan of Coffeebar in Truckee for a while, so was excited to hear of a Reno location.  It was curious that they didn't open faster (sat dormant for six months), but seeing the space now, it makes sense.
They've taken the whole western side of the building (not sure what was here before), and the space that was formerly Bibo appears to be dominated by a large kitchen now.  There's 3 or 4 four tops up front, and a large TV that was showing the Niners-Seahawks game.  Two large refrigerated cases in an L-shape, counter to order from, and then a gigantic espresso machine - cases and counter are probably a good 25 feet.  Back of the space has lots of tables, probably a half-dozen four tops as well as some counter top seating.  Exposed ceilings and ductwork - probably close to 14 feet, so the space looks big.  White subway tile behind the counter, orange pain on the non-brick walls, and a large bent stainless/LED light fixture in the back.  For those familiar with the former Bibo, this is a huge change, as the space is massive, and seems like it'll be a great spot to get some work done.  
Another big change from Bibo is that there's wireless internet (and plenty of tables and seating to camp out with a laptop).
I had a large Americano while I typed this up. 
Rad new location in the old Southwest that while I'm sure will have some holdouts due to all the drama around Bibo and the former location, seems like they've got enough good things going that they'll do all right.
Friendly baristas and great coffee. Since their expansion it has been a great place to hangout and wait for coffee.
Love their coffee and vibe. The breakfast food was awesome as well. The outdoor seating area is super nice and feels very calming. Big interior as well.

It's like everything you try is your new favorite habit. Such amazing service, hospitality, and most importantly tastes. I made myself sick drinking so much nitro draft late it was so good.... don't tell anybody but I'd do it again too.

This is probably one of my favorite boba places in Reno, Nevada. The service is great and the workers there are always so friendly and welcoming. Even when it's busy they make the drinks pretty fast, while still making them taste good. I would definitely recommend this place! 
I have not tried the food, but I'm sure it's just as good

Supreme everything!!! Distinctive customer service. 
Sublime new ownership. This is the town's jewel.
I vigorously recommend it.

While I enjoy both French Press locations, this one is my favorite.  It's a lot bigger and has patio seating in front of the entrance.  You can lounge there on Sundays and think about scheduling for a haircut at the Paul Mitchell school across the street.
The coffee here is excellent, and the Barista always friendly.  I usually order the Tres Leche drink or cappuccino.  Both help when I need to get some serious studying done or walk the mall area.  While the drinks here tend to be more on the pricier side, I think of it as a treat.  A place to go when I'm too lazy to bring out my french press and make coffee for myself.  Since I no longer live in close proximity to Santa Barbara, I will miss this place.  So for those who live nearby, you're very lucky.

This place had spaces to sit and hang out but it seemed like they were trying too hard to make it a "hang out" place than a nice one. It was too noisy from the music inside and the cars and noises outside seeming even louder. My white mocha was not bad but my fiance's pour over took to long and tasted a little burnt I don't think they really knew how to make it. We went there to try a new place but we will never go there again.

I think I'm over Natural Cafe. The other day I ordered my usual SB Veggie Grill, and realized it no longer comes with the tahini sauce. It's just grilled veggies on brown rice. When I asked what happened to the sauce the employee said it now costs $2 extra.  It's already $11.50 for the plate (grilled veggies and tofu on a bed of brown rice). Unless there's something about tahini being super expensive that I don't know about, I don't get why you would take away a sauce from a menu item and then charge for it. I think that's bad business.

I am completely and totally obsessed. Yesterday was my third time here, and as always, the service is kind and welcoming, the environment is clean and comfortable, and the food tastes as good as it feels. Get ANYTHING with the tamari mushrooms. (I love the nacho salad or the terriyaki bowl) They are so flavorful and wonderful, they've been haunting my dreams.

101 was delightful! Stopped by after working up an appetite running errands in town and we happened to show up during happy hour - two for one drinks (possibly also applies to alcoholic drinks, but we both got boba teas instead)
The scallion pancakes were a perfect appetizer. They came out hot, crispy, and a little oily, delicious.
The tonkatsu chicken and fried tofu bao were both delicious. All the condiments on their bao make for a sort of savory, sort of sweet flavor combo (cilantro, sweet sauce, and a few other things I don't remember off the top of my head)
The popcorn chicken was also excellent. Tiny, very crispy bits of chicken served with rice and a potato salad. I didn't try the potato salad, but heard it was more of a macaroni salad. 
I highly recommend Taiwan 101. Food is cooked quickly, staff are nice, and everything I've tried so far is absolutely delicious.
A new pho restaurant that opened up tastes pretty good and pretty good service. However, not as good as places back in oc but pretty good compared to other places in goleta
This restaurant has the best Chinese food in Reno. We always eat in this restaurant when we come to Reno. Their service is also excellent!!

I go to Coffeebar at least 2-3 times a month and it's one of my favorite places to suggest when I get to choose where to go for a meeting.  One of the reasons it is my favorite over other coffee options is because of their big food menus.  I'm not extremely picky about what kind of coffee I want or like so a lot of times I go to Coffeebar just to eat!  They have a great crepes and pastries and my favorite is the nutella/banana/strawberry crepe! 
One of the other reasons that I like Coffeebar so much is because they have a beautiful outdoor patio in the back with a gorgeous big wood table.  I love sitting out here in the summer! 
The only reason this is a 4 star review and not a 5 star review is because of the service.  Everyone who works there is nice but not often as helpful as I need them to be.  For example, last week I ordered a hot tea there for the first time and it came in a weird metal cylinder that took up the entire space of the mug.  I had no idea what it was so I picked it up and gave myself a steam burn.  I was able to go up to the counter again and ask how to use it but she said "oh they really should have asked if you knew how to use it when you ordered!" - I agree.  
Overall love this place and will continue to visit it frequently!

I was beyond excited for a Korean restaurant to open since the only one in town is Hana Garden and I was not disappointed. I came in with my sister for dinner tonight and since both of us have not been here before we asked for recommendations. Their top 3 classic bibimbap were the bulgogi beef, spicy pork and teriyaki chicken. My sister ordered the bulgogi and I ordered the teriyaki chicken. We were told that all bibimbap comes with miso soup which was nice. With yelp check-in, you get 50% off the second bowl. 
Let me just say that I love the location and the decor of the place. It's very aesthetic and modern. There are plenty of tables and bar like seating. Did I mention the staffs? Well the staffs are super friendly and helpful. 
The food is delicious with a few different kind of mixing sauce to choose from. My sister and I love spicy food so we both chose the Korean spicy sauce but we mixed in a little of the super spicy sauce because we wanted to feel more of a kick. 
We'll definitely will be returning to try other things on the menu.

Thai 101 is my go-to boba shop! They have a great selection of traditional milk teas as well as fruit slushes and juices that you can always add boba to. I usually get the Thai milk tea with boba and it is WONDERFUL. It's not overly sweet but still has that authentic Thai tea taste. Sometimes I switch it up and get a fruit slush with boba, especially in the summer.
I'll definitely have to stop in for lunch or dinner sometime.

Coffeebar Reno is an excellent place to 
A. Get coffee, espresso, tea drinks made to perfection
B. Enjoy Lunch or Breakfast with a friend or family member with plenty of Vegan and Glutten free options
C. Do A and B while checking all your emails, listen to music on your headphones, write a paper, do your work in a nice enjoyable atmosphere.
The food here was great everything in the display case I wanted to try. Everything coming out of the kitchen looked neat and prepared delicately for maximum enjoyment the chefs were doing a great job on a Monday 10/21. On top of the good food and great service the space was huge. There were plenty of open seats to seat yourself for both small and big groups. 
Not pictured was the amazing Espresso Bar. Wow!!! Try two!!
Vegan and Vegetarian
Good for small and large groups
Patio
Cafe
Baked goods

I've had Superstitions Java a handful of times now because it's close to my work and I gotta say--I have never had a bad drink! I've tried the Love Potion #9 (horchata goodness), a dirty chai, a lavender latte, the purple reign (an ube latte) and they are all SO good! The only one I wasn't as crazy about is the lavender latte because before I mixed it, it kinda tasted like soap, but other than that they've all been great. Everyone is always friendly, the decor is fun, space seems clean, etc. If you haven't been, it's definitely worth checking out!
I wish I could have this for breakfast every day! So tasty, healthy & refreshing. Great comfortable environment. Highly recommend this place!
We're from Taiwan and we would recommend this restaurant to others. The food is authentic(most of them) and the staff is fairly nice too. Like this place a lot.

Time to update past review.    The service had definitely improved!    Being on the way home every day, I pass by and have been swinging in for a quick drink.   Much quicker than the past 3 months!!   
The afternoon barista's are getting better.  
The large selection of holiday beverages keep me wanting to go back and try new things.   
Make sure you ask for it to be extra hot if you want to feel some warmth going down your throat.  
The new gingerbread latte has just the right amount of ginger and cinnamon.
They have no problems giving your pup a cup of whipped cream "pupachino".   Just ask when you get to the drive up.

Very cute place to go to for a hang out or chat with friends. But I stopped by to get a oolong milk tea with boba. The door was labeled best milk tea but I wouldn't consider the best. One thing that I was disappointed was that they didn't have grass jelly. The topping options didn't have a lot of choices.
Very delicious make your own hash in Santa Barbara! Everything was fresh and delicious. Get there early as the line can tend to get long!

This a hangout for homeless bums and druggies. Panhandlers stand around in front of the store mgt. does nothing about it. Don't stop there,go to a casino and avoid the danger. They should just close down. Cold mornings are the worst smelly loser just fill the seats. STAY AWAY!!!!

I lived in Santa Barbara back in the early 90's and have been back many times since then.  I've passed this place a hundred times and never stopped in.   For spring break I took my kids to Santa Barbara and finally stopped by for lunch.  We were seated outside immediately.  The waitress came by shortly after we sat down and took our order.  The kids each had a burger and fries and I tried the cobb salad.  The food was good.  I won't say its the best lunch we've ever had but it was really good.  I will definitely come here again.  The burgers and fries were tasty and my salad was fresh and a good portion.
If you need a dependable place to eat, give it a try.  I loved the outside seating and the old school ambiance.

In today's economy, wanting more bang for your $ is the norm... I learned the hard way. Portions are always enough.  My desires for a large size put me over the top.  I ate about half of my cup and tossed the rest away.  Quality was good, can't complain about fruit and grains. Can't really screw that one up at all.  Just put it all in a bowl and consume.
Really liked this place.  Off the beaten path, nice pleasant atmosphere, great outdoor space.   I had a very good tea and scone.

Wow.... just wow. I have been here along time ago and it was good(nothing too memorable) but I came again today to try it out and I am in SHOCK. Not only was all of the food DELICIOUS, but the service was just amazing! The girl who took my order was named Leah if I remember correctly, and she was so attentive, helpful, made a great latte, and so cute! I would recommend the housemade hummus and the avocado toast... so yummy.  I will definitely be back(hopefully on a Monday so that Leah can take my order:)

I love this coffee shop.  It has the best environment and the best tasting coffee.  My son really enjoys there hot chocolate as well.  I love the side room where you can hold coffee appts or small networking meetings.  I really like that they are close to my work as well.

Amazing bowls and smoothies! Very quick and easy for students that have a time limit between classes or are always on the go. They are extremely delicious and filling but a little on the pricier side so just be fare warned about that. Would definitely recommend that Protein Bowl with Peanut Butter!

Food is picking up from there old natural but bland style. If you try s special, they are creative and tasty, except pasta because they think "al dente"something a body shop beats out of your car. 
Besides pasta, things are very tasty. Desserts are terrific

Very disappointed with the chicken pad Thai. There just wasn't enough flavor. I've had a lot better elsewhere, but then again this is a Vietnamese food restaurant and not a Thai food restaurant. However, their pho soups are pretty good.
Pleasantly surprised by this unassuming spot at a strip mall in Sparks. Coffee was fantastic. Food was really good. Had the pho, spring rolls and banh mi. Brought, clean interior and friendly staff

Meh.  
Maybe I caught them on an off day, but the Bun I had (chicken + egg roll) was really bland.  I've had this dish at least 100 times at several dozen places (including in Vietnam) and this was definitely the least flavorful and interesting.   Normally I love the interplay of warm grilled meat, room temperature noodles and cold crisp veggies.  This basically just tasted like a bland bowl of cold slippery noodles with a few random bits of meat and iceberg lettuce thrown in.   Uninspired and totally lacking the vibrancy that I usually love about Vietnamese food. 
Somehow the overall effect was just kind of cold, greasy and fishy tasting (and I'm not talking about the fish sauce that is served with it).  It was actually off-putting.   I was starved, though so I ate most of it anyway. 
The service was great (very attentive despite being very busy), but I definitely won't be coming back for the Bun.   Looking around me everyone else was having Pho, so maybe that is the better choice...

One of my fav places for coffee! They definitely know their stuff about coffee and have food as well. A great meeting spot, as they do have wifi. Just be aware that it is busy and you may be cramped, looking for an outlet, or on the move for open tables. A little bit pricey for a college student.

Great new place! The food is VERY fresh!  Will definitely return often!
Plenty of parking so don't worry about it being downtown!

It's a relatively new coffee place out here in Reno, but is definitely gaining popularity!! They majorly rely on drive-thru customers and I've almost never seen their drive-thru empty. 
I went to this shop with my mom, who is not the biggest fan of coffee but she absolutely loved the flavors they had. We tried he macadamia nut - chocolate flavored coffee and it was amazing!! (Tip: do try it with the whipped cream added). A large coffee would be about 7$ so it's pretty reasonable.
I've seen 2 outlets of theirs, one on Sierra center parkway and one on south Virginia street(the more popular one).
Their staff was young and very courteous which made the overall experience very good indeed.
Great coffee, great service, highly recommend!

My husband and I love their bibimbap. We were so happy to have found a Korean food spot here in Reno. We get it delivered all the time. I do want to share something though, and hope that the company sees this. 
WARNING: DO NOT MICROWAVE THE MISO SOUP CUPS! 
Company should put some sort of labeling that it is flammable. Good thing I didn't leave while it was in the microwave.
Not friendly at all. Girl forgot to give me my cup so I asked for a cup. She asked me questions like I took a cup. Is she for real? Bad customer service. Has gone downhill since new ownership.

My husband and I were visiting from Seattle. We are big fans of açaí bowls and have tried countless bowls across multiple states. While the bowl itself was okay (I've had much fresher and flavorful bowls elsewhere), the service was terrible. The wait was 40 minutes and two of our four bowls were the wrong size. However, it was the lack of care and attention to my food allergies which precipitated this review. I cannot eat gluten and paid for the gluten-free granola. When retrieving my order, I asked multiple times which bowl was which to confirm I was getting the one that was gluten-free. It wasn't until I was halfway into my bowl I realized I was told the wrong bowl and ended up feeling terrible all day. I would caution about going here if you have any food allergies or sensitivities as I do not have confidence in their customer service.
Great place and awesome food. Love the apparel and bigtruck coffee bar hats are sweet (although I didn't see any this trip in. I want to buy some for my family) great place that I highly recommend!

New favorite breakfast spot in Reno. Great selection including vegetarian and vegan options on their everyday menu that aren't afterthoughts, and tempting specials. Excellent service, cool space, great food, fresh ingredients, solid prices, good music (selection and conversation-friendly volume). Husband got breakfast tacos, I got vegan French toast with almond butter and banana batter. Both were great. We'll definitely be back.
Great customer service, food was ok I had the "Breakfast Sando" and asked for potatoes instead of the salad, potatoes were great but the sandwich itself wasn't

Some of the best Brunch I've had in town! Our waiter Coen was an excellent server and very polite and friendly. He checked in on us regularly to make sure we had plenty of coffee and such. The atmosphere was great and the staff overall is very friendly. I would recommend this place to anyone who has not gone.

Every order is a new adventure here. The menu is so expansive, and for an Asian food lover like myself, that means endless opportunity. 

I try not to order the same dishes twice, but the food here is so good, I can't help but have a few favorites. The popcorn chicken must be included in every meals the light and crunchy coating is seasoned with some sweet warm spices that make the chicken delicious all on its own, but if you dip it in the sauce, it's next level. I also have a hard time skipping over dishes in the basil sauce, which usually is chicken, but this time I tried the king mushrooms. These are meaty and delicious, stir fried in a slightly sweet, spicy and savory sauce studded with whole cloves of garlic, big pieces of ginger and chili!

The Authentic Taiwanese section is always good for a few foodie thrills. This time around we tried the house style braised pork belly. I'd say this one was good, but I missed the sauce and braised veg I enjoy with other preparations.

My favorite section of the menu is the "appetizers". New items are always added here, and they're typically great. This time we went with the braised Napa cabbage (so savory, delicious, and full of umami) and the omelette with salty daikon. Both home runs. The sweetness of the egg mixed with seasoning and the salty pickled daikon was a great contrast to a lot of the richer dishes we ordered, and adding the leftovers to fried rice was amazing! 

If you haven't been here, you absolutely must go. Check out the photos to see all we ordered this go round! This is one of my all time favorite eats in Reno!

Friday morning, only 2 other patrons in the place and it took about 5 minutes to even get a menu. When she put the menus down she didnt ask if we wanted anything to drink. We finally get drinks and my coffee sits empty the entire time until i wave her down everytime i want a refill. My omelet came with olives which i did not order. our food took about 20 minutes to arrive which in a diner with 2 other customers should not be the case. Both of our breakfasts were very mediocre. The cook came out and apologized for the olives but no discount or anything of that nature was offered. The cook, presumably the owner was very friendly but the server was an overall fail and the food wasnt much better. This is a pass in the future for me.

The space is huge and inviting with reasonably comfy tables and chairs; a nice upgrade from the Truckee shop. Lots of nice decorative details too, like the mosaic lion on the wall. It looks like they're still landscaping out back which should be a nice outdoor space in the spring. I shared a latte with the wife and thought it was great and fresh. Kids hot chocolate for the kid was tasty enough. 
The big ding was for a $6.75 calzone (made next door,I believe) that they reheated on the panini press. While the filling was tasty enough, the reheating seared and slightly warmed a  chewy, stale crust. This awful texture voided anything good going inside the thing. While the pre-assembled sandwiches seem to hold up to the refrigeration and reheating, I would highly recommend coffeebar nix the reheated calzone idea; it just doesn't work.

I go here quite often and the service is always good and the employees are always kind and happy. They make every experience there enjoyable. The coffee and food are always delightful. 5 out of 5, would recommend.

Decide to try this place as it was the closes one near our area with 4 star review . Well, extremely disappointed compare to all other pho places we've been to. Very short staff, very stingy with toppings and napkins. My order was wrong but decided to have what was delivered because we had a long wait and the guy taking the orders was the same person preparing some orders .  I think I might of been overcharged( they didn't present us with a ticket . Same guy just clicked his computer and gave me my total at the register.)or this is very expensive compare to legit Vietnamese restaurants. $34  for 2 regular pho as nd 2 egg roll s.

I've only been into the brick and mortar restaurant a couple of times, I usually get it delivered through ubereats. But the couple of times I did visit the store, the staff were very friendly and helpful. They were able to make good suggestions on what to order and what sauces to use. And they were very knowledgeable about the different Korean dishes. I've had every meat stop bibim-bob on the menu and they are all absolutely delicious! My favorite is the bulgogi though, the meat is tender and thin with jut the right amount of seasonings. I love that they offer so many different options for dietary restrictions as well. You can order most bowls gluten free or without rice. I always get the japchae. They make some of my favorite japchae I've ever had. I've also heard the potstickers are to die for! I'll have to try them for myself soon.
Amazing food, always satisfied! Great people and service. Try it, if you have never had Korean, give it a try will not disappoint.

It's been a long time since I've been here and the burgers were very tasty and the ingredients were fresh. Not as laid back as it once was but neither is Goleta. The prices here are still a notch lower than the Habit.

I guess being from California, I am spoiled by great Chinese food. This place was ok. My family and I ordered beef noodle (it was ok), scallion pancake (soggy, not crispy), popcorn chicken (decent), and a salt and pepper pork chop (could be better). I also ordered a boba black tea (not good, boba was over cooked. Not good. For a Taiwanese place in Reno, it was not bad but I would probably try somewhere else first before coming back here.

THIS PLACE IS DOPE. How their food is so good and so reasonably priced is beyond me. Their prosciutto sandwich transported me to a different dimension the first time I ate it, it was so good. Obviously the crack bowls are fantastic and get that lemon tahini sauce. Good god.

Nice spot in Santa Barbara to have a quick brekky. I got 2 eggs and bacon and coffee. 


It wasn't bad! But it also wasn't amazing.

My absolute favorite spot. So many yummy teas and the way they serve it makes me
Happy. Location is beyond perfect and the pastry sate like nothing you've ever seen anywhere. I could spend all damn day here in a second. Love this place

This place is a Gem!
First of all, I had known this place for their baked goods, specifically their Macaroons.Being one of the few places in town that I know for sure had them. But I had no idea about the cafe, that they had here. 
I didn't want anything too heavy although they  had ordered the Pico De Gallo Eggs Benedict. and I'm glad I did. It came topped with avocado, and Haus-made salsa and hollandaise. The avocado was ripe, and super fresh.The salsa wasn't over overbearing in spice, but still came full in flavor which is what I was hoping for. They hit it right on the nail with the Benedict. I absolutely loved it.
It came with a side of cottage potatoes which were probably the best spuds Ive had to date. To my surprise, from the looks of the potatoes, I didn't think they'd be so delicious. I loved them.The texture...The Flavor...  Cooked with the skin on, the potatoes were crisp and well seasoned on the outside, and cooked so well that they melt in your mouth. Definitely will be one of my go to dishes.
I'll definitely be back
I Saw that they had a pot pie, on their menu. Im for sure gonna try that on my next visit.
Being that the place is a bakery, I for sure had to pick up some dessert on my way out. Grabbed a few Macaroons (Pistachio, Hazelnut, and Oreo Cookie) on the way out.

Pretty good coffee! They managed to make handlebar coffee taste better here than it does at handlebar. Hoping they may take a hint and start using Sightglass or other espresso instead, but they do a pretty good job with what they've been given. Best coffee we had so far visiting sb.

Yummy. This is the best place to eat for this type of cuisine. Very small place but they seemed to fit us in in a reasonable amount of time. Generous portions ! Broken English but still understood us very well. Shrimp and vegetables is my favorite !!
Excellent coffee! Friendly staff! They have tons of room to work or just sit and talk with friends. Matt is amazing! He's friendly and makes a killer latte.

Great service! It was our first time in and the cashier was very welcoming, explained how it works and was efficient. Our food came out quickly and was delicious with generous portions. The vibe was really nice inside, there was plenty of seating, and everything looked really clean. 
If we're ever passing through reno again, we would definitely go back!
Amazing vegan donuts and pastries and great coffee, too. Really good place to do work due to lots of outlets and speedy wifi. The staff are very charming and fun. Definitely recommend!!!

Been wanting to try Our Daily Bread since it appeared on a nearby corner. Was disappointed with my first visit. Terrible place to sit on the corner of De la Vina and Alamar. The food was a bit overpriced and it took 25 minutes to get an omlet. There was no service. Cute orange chairs though and a good local brand.

Great service great coffee and the
Salami sandwich with arugula was awesome
I ordered the iced mocha 
Great place just to relax

This place is the best! 10/10 would recommend to a friend. 
I tell everyone to go here and it's truly a unique coffee experience. If you've ever been the Philz in the bay area, their process is similar. 
The jet fuel, fog lifter and Kenya are some of my favorites blends. They do a great bulletproof coffee and I can't wait to drink more mint mojitos in the summer. 
The owner is so friendly and remembers everyone. She's the best. I love the staff here and it's truly a gem of Reno.
Love this local spot with amazing grilled fish and of course the burger! Great patio setting , relaxing and casual. Oh, and there is a full bar!

Stop here for great Mexican food! Yummy guacamole, salsa bar, and chips. Nice tacos (hard and soft options), rice, and beans. You get great sized portions! Sitting outside is nice. Great road trip stop!

New building means a new review!  For those of you who've been looking, Reno Coffee Company has relocated to a much expanded store on the corner of Wells and Vassar.  And while I'm sad to see the very lovely, quaint little store go, it is still always a good thing when a local business can grow.  The new building is a serious upgrade from the original location, which clears the way for such luxuries as tables and chairs and couches that let people sit and enjoy their coffee like an actual café.  But rest assured, the same quirky décor and aesthetics are here, and more importantly, so is the amazing coffee you've come to expect.

Here, every beverage is made to order.  Pick your bean variety, form their selection of about a dozen or so with different origins, roast levels, and flavor profiles, and watch as the staff grind up your individual portion, and use their nifty counter top setup to make an amazing cup of pour-over.  After that, you get to choose how you customize your drink, from the type of creamer, the type of sweetener, and additions of spices, in order to tailor it to just the way you like it.  In addition to the option to build your own cup, they also have a small menu of house specialty drinks you can enjoy, too.  The Morning Mojito is a popular choice, sweetened with agave nectar and mint leaves.  But I would highly recommend the Chocolate Pour, which is a most excellent mocha-esque drink.  There is also a fridge case with teas and kombucha, and should you come later in the afternoon or evening, you can also indulge in the recent additions to the menu of wine and beer, both on tap and in cans.  One thing you will not find on their menu, however, is espresso-drinks.  But honestly, you won't even miss your lattes and cappuccinos, as this place shows you just how good brewed coffee can be.  There is also, as of yet, no food options either, which is fine by me, as it makes this a literal "coffee shop" in that it is just a place to enjoy a quality beverage.

As prices go, we all know the old joke about paying a lot for "JUST" a cup of coffee.  However, that is actually sort of true here, as there are certainly no cheap drinks.  Expect to pay at least $4 for a cup, with prices going up from there depending on the size you get, or what beverage you choose.  However, before you let the sticker shock turn you off, I would say it is well worth the price for this phenomenal quality, and is comparable prices to most espresso drinks anyway.  Beer starts at around $6 per pint, and wine at about $8 per glass.  And you can take home a whole bag of their coffee, whole beans or ground, starting around $15 and up.

Service here is exceptionally friendly and courteous, and what really elevates them over a lot of other coffeehouses in this town.  As for speed, do not expect them to just pour you out a cup, as it takes a few minutes to properly brew up your individual orders.  I will say one of the very few drawbacks to this place is that this method can, at times, lead to a bit more of a wait if you stop by when a lot of people are in line ordering drinks.  But to me, it is well worth the wait.

The building itself is bright and open, with parking usually pretty easily obtained from various street spaces out front and around the corner, though be cautious if getting in and out of cars if you are parked along Wells itself.

All in all, Reno Coffee Company continues to prove why they are one of the absolute best places in town to get your caffeine fix.  It is certainly one of the more unique places to grab a cup-o-joe, and I will certainly continue to make them a regular stop.

30 minutes for a to go cappuccino?  This is absurd.  One suggestion for a more efficient way to make coffee and get it out to your customers is not to fill up multiple to go orders before bringing them out to the customers.   By the time I was able to enjoy my first sip it was luke warm.  Will not be coming back to this place ever again!

Nice service, nice atmosphere, great coffee, fabulous food. Very young crowd. Kid-friendly. Counter service, great menu including lots of breakfast staples, kids options, and make your own hash. I ordered the hash with sweet potato and peppers, sage sausage, spinach, tomatoes, scrambled eggs and herb aioli. My husband ordered the huevos rancheros. Both were delicious. My picky son ordered the kids grilled cheese and it was a hit. Homemade OJ was excellent. Park in the lot across the street. Great spot in SB.

I had breakfast their the other day and thought it to be a really nice place.  The breakfast was A1 with very good patty sausage, eggs, and home made hashbrowns.  I definitely will return.  Keep up the good work.......

column1: They don't have any indoor seating
column2: so it wouldn't make a great place to study or hang out. You get two choices... it's either the drive-thru or the outdoor walk-up menu.

column8: Great breakfast spot off State Street that was close to where we were staying in the Funk Zone. You order at the counter and then grab a seat. Our food took a while to come out but it was worth the wait. We ordered the egg white frittata and the chorizo hash which were both equally great; however, the real show stopper was my iced vanilla latte. We'll definitely come back next time we're in town.

Neat place. Fair prices. Nice menu. Noisy. Overcooked meals. Service so-so. Artichoke appetizers loked great but had been steamed for hours.Grilled asparagus was wonderful. NY strip steak obviously par cooked and then finished off when ordered by diner. Orderd medium it arrived pink but very chewy and absolutely no juices flowed when cut into. Disappointing. The shoe string potatoes sounded great but tasted and looked as if they were straight from the box. My wife's mahi-mahi was burnt on the bottom and over done. Her mashed potatoes were the best part of the meal. A dinner companion's salmon looked terrific and she enjoyed it.  Easy to park in public lot kitty-korner from restaurant. If you like uneven, overcooked food this is your cup of tea. In my opinion there are at least seven better restaurants within a five minute stroll from here.

Everything was fantastic. From the friendly staff to the wonderful healthy food. I had the frittata which was very tasty and the wife had the grits hash. 
The music is old school which is fun. I know it seems ridiculous but I have to give a thumbs up for the napkins. They are thick and sturdy unlike other places where you have to use four since they just fall apart. 
They also make a good cup of Joe.
We will definitely be back - I wish we were a little closer so that we could come more often but we will for sure be back.

A delicious way to start the day, with a very friendly and helpful staff.
Our server Julio could not have been nicer. He got us off to good start with his food recommendations, and kept our coffee mugs full and hot.
We usually dive in to the tasty hash dishes, but today seemed like a good morning for their Fish Tacos, and Huevos Rancheros. Highly recommend both. 
Also a great way to start the day, with a public parking lot right across State Street on Gutierrez, and in between the Funk Zone and all that fun shopping on lower State Street.
Had the popcorn chicken, it was incredible. (Just make sure to order extra peanut sauce). Great service also.
Ive been here for a few times already. And I just love this place. Love their spicy basil chicken, bobas, and all. The service here is so nice. My favorite place to have asian food ;) thank you.

I've been waiting for a long time for a good boba place to open, and this place passes all of the tests!! I ordered a specialty drink, just to see what they were made of - the strawberry shortcake. Milk smoothie with strawberry boba and jelly, topped with graham crumbles. I added some Matcha pudding, since it peaked my interest. I'm glad I ordered 50% sweetness, because the jelly's had a lot of sweetness already. But it was all so tasty!!! Definitely coming back to check out the rest of the extensive options. Oh! And to try their shaved ice!

Don't be fooled by the occasional low rating on Yelp. This store is amazing. It's a new addition to their other store located on State, and they are getting into the groove of how this store flows (seems to get much more busier!). 
Parking get's congested especially on Farmer's Market days (Sat. and Tues.) but there is a paid lot just across the street that you can easily use if you can't find any in theirs. Staff is friendly and knows their stuff, but they won't look down on you if you aren't a coffee connoisseur! And its clean. Drinks are consistently good, but if you have any trouble don't be afraid to ask for a replacement. Love the French Press!

I love when you get to Rave about a place or someone that works there.  This store has friendly, kind, knowledgeable and professional employees. 
Looking for gas, snacks or something to eat? Or maybe just a Slurpee? This convenience store has something for everyone. Slurpee's are usually my reason for stopping here. My family has been getting Slurpee's from this store for many years. 
Being that this store is in Nevada there are several slot machines. Sometimes I can win enough to pay for my Slurpee's.  Conveniently there is a Red Box in front of the store.

We like the food here and all the other waiters and waitresses are very nice and friendly.
This one star is because of a waitress with ponytail who has really bad attitude. Maybe it's because we don't speak Cantonese, she serves us very impatiently.
We arrived at 11am as soon as they opened. But she served us later than all the other tables of customers who arrived later than us. We told her that we're ready to order, but she still served people who speak Cantonese first, and asked us to just wait. 
When ordering, we asked her if she had any recommendations. She just said "if you are not ready, order later." Then she walked away. We were very disappointed at her attitude.
As soon as we finished our food, she immediately walked to us, and asked us to check. We were having lunch with a friend who we hadn't seen for a year, so we wanted to chat for a while. So we said "maybe give us a few more minutes" Then she said "please leave immediately after finishing your lunch, because we still have people waiting outside." Although all the other tables are still chatting. But we had to check immediately and leave. 
We feel that we are discriminated by her just because we don't speak Cantonese, although we can speak English and mandarin very well. I believe that all people should be served equally no matter which languages that can speak. And in US, a Taiwanese restaurant shouldn't discriminate people who can speak English or mandarin.
And again, all the other people there are friendly. And the foods are good. So I still think that you can try it if you can speak Cantonese or the woman with ponytail is not there.

Wow - who's the girl that's super rude ?? We usually love this place BUT !!! We recently came in for breakfast while visiting SB and asked to not have onions on the special - I understand no substitutions to specials - I only asked if I could get it without onions - maybe they are sprinkled on top - I don't know - instead of the girl at the counter explaining to me whether the onions are cooked in or not she just rudely said "nope" when I asked if she could explain, she said " no changes to specials, chef's rules" without even asking the chef. Whenever we drive through or stay over in SB, we always come here - here's the things that aren't good:
1. Always cold in the morning (outside is warmer then inside on most days) 
2. Wait staff has gotten rude over the last few months 
3. Takes forever when slightly busy 
4. And then they can't cut out onions on a dish ???
Definitely noticing a decline. Not sure if I'll be coming back to this place again.

When we came to the Paradise Cafe on a Thursday evening, the place was packed. We had reservations at 7:45pm. We came a little before hand for the server to tell us that the party before us was finishing up. It turned out to be at least a 20-30 minute wait. The workers were very apologetic though and gave us free appetizers, which was nice. 
The service was generally slow, and the waitress kept forgetting one of our party's margaritas. 
The food was ok. I had the roasted eggplant sandwich, which was tasty but hard to eat. Another person had the shrimp salad- which came out with the saddest, tiniest shrimp. The salad also looked kind of dead- with wilted looking vegetables. And the people who ordered the burgers thought they were good. Is it a worthy $10 burger though, I'm not sure. 
Overall, it was a pleasant evening because that was mostly because of the company and cool breeze that came in from the patio. I am still a little perplexed about how crowded it was, because I do not think I would rush back or wait so long for average food and slow service.

Surprised to find a Taiwanese restaurant in Reno so it's a must try when we're here just for for the rib cook-off.  It's pretty good for Reno, however,  it's not as good as Arcadia/Monterey Park Taiwanese cuisine.  Suggestion:  Add Taiwanese shaved ice to your menu.
Excellent food! Beef pancake is a must try, along with any of the bento boxes, and of course no meal is complete without boba! Love that that they are open late (until midnight) on the weekends.

The servers & managers are honestly the nicest people ever. Mr. Lee and Miss Kelly are the cutest and friendliest workers ever as well! They just speak really loudly, which gives the impression that they're rude...but that's how a lot of Vietnamese people speak! 
Service: A lot of people complain about the service, but do keep in mind that they are very understaffed. It is extremely difficult to both cook and serve at the same time, especially on busy days. They really do try their best! Pho takes HOURS to prepare and the broth takes a lot of work to maintain-- this goes for most Vietnamese food. Cut them some slack. They even offer free samples! And the other workers are extremely sweet as well.
As for the food: my boyfriend and I love their beef fried rice. It's simple and yummy. Their pho is delicious on cold, SB days when you're too lazy to go out (and of course...they're the best cure for your IV hangovers). I also love love love their coffee milk tea!!! Their banh mi isn't how they're traditionally made in most SoCal places (cold cut meat, veggies, etc) but their beef banh mi is still really really good!

I love me some good coffee with a hip vibe! This place is hands down the best coffee spot in town. They also have excellent breakfast burritos and tasty quiche. My wife loves their hot mocha and I go with the iced mocha. Also has a lively atmosphere with good energy! Reminds me of a Seattle feel. We need more coffeebar locations.

Great coffee, hip atmosphere, fresh air outside seating, great people watching
I will come back for their Matcha Green Tea!

I was staying in Reno and went for a morning run - wanting to check out Coffeebar Reno...it did not disappoint!  Great friendly service, open at 6am, and yummy peanut butter energy balls!  Highly recommend!

Much as I love this place, returning here after a couple of years in Melbourne Australia, I now find the coffee rather weak and tasteless. Still far far better than Starbucks and most of the terrible American coffee though.  Very nice friendly staff. BTW Wireless is pretty slow.
Great coffee, I had the orange blossom iced coffee. Delicious! The people, could be a little friendlier.
Good food, they didn't rush us when we were eating last closing. The fish tacos were BOMB!

Each week my work team does a 'Feed Your Feelings Friday', and this week we spent it at the Cat Therapy Cafe. It was the best group session we've ever had: so peaceful and fun, loving and nourishing for the spirit. The cats are amazing and wonderful, and the staff takes great care of them. It was reflective, calming, and thoroughly enjoyable. We will be back!

Avocado with boba is my favorite to buy from this place.  But after the pandemic, they made changes.  They now offer "extra" boba and charge extra, which is fine.  But the last couple of times that i ordered avocado with boba, i noticed it's not as sweet anymore.  Are we supposed to request "add sweet" if we want the same taste like it was before?

This place is great to grab a healthy, quick bite right by State St in Santa Barbara. Their açaí bowls were huge and super filling and they have a lot of unique smoothie flavors. Also, I tried one of their breakfast bowls and they were great! Definitely a more sophisticated version of your average oatmeal. If I went back, the bowls would definitely be my first choice.

I liked Intermezzo. It's small and cozy. It's a casual meeting place. We sat outside and enjoyed the flash fried cauliflower with capers and Parmesan cheese. It was excellent. We also had salads with the pretzel bread. The fresh ahi tuna on the salad was delicious. The service was good and the waitress was helpful. The food is served extremely hot. I would go back.

I was hesitant to write such a negative review for a place I've been here dozens of times. I reliably go here for bibimbap but unfortunately, this is happening. I've been here in person before and I loved the decor, miso soup, and selection of sauces. So I decided to order off UberEats. I don't know what happened but my meal was pretty subpar. 
When I order tofu bibimbap, I expect the carrots to be shredded. Instead, they just threw in 4 baby carrots in my dish. That's a little odd. Along with that, the broccoli and cauliflower were just not cooked at all. I could be mistaken but I think those are supposed to be steamed. Lastly, there was no egg, spinach, or cucumber. Those vegetables are advertised in the UberEats selection yet they are not there. This was extremely lackluster.
Not only that, but my friend, who ordered the japchae meal only got 1 baby carrot. If you do not have the proper ingredients, please list it somewhere. Make the menu item invalid. Just don't let me order it only for us to be disappointed. 
I do like this place. I'm sad I had such a bad experience this time around. This experience was 3 stars, but due to my numerous good experiences, I decided to put 4. Hopefully, next time will be better!

Reno has lots of coffee shops and they're all great and have different strengths. Old worlds coffee may be the best tasting depending who you ask, but their nitro latte is the best coffee drink in town, and that's a fact. You can google it.
Small interior, loud wood floor and bar, tasty treats, outdoor seating in the summer. You can see Bibo across the street, so if you crave something not on the menu, you could always walk over, but if your already in line, commit gahdammit.

Food was good a little pricey in my opinion, but the quality was good. Been living in SB for a while and never noticed this place because of its "hidden" location next to Casablanca. My wife and I agreed that our favorite part of our experience was the service. Servers were very kind and attentive. The restaurant was also very clean and had a great vibe.
We will definitely visit again!

Man I just can't give more than three stars. The service was good, the pastries were excellent, but the actual coffees weren't anything to write home about. I had a vanilla latte that wasn't all that good. My fiancé had the sage infused maple latte that tasted like the inside of a thanksgiving turkey's asshole. I really wanted so much more from this place. Maybe we'll try again.

WORST PLACE EVER! DRUG NEEDLES IN BATHROOM. Horrible place! So dirty! Tables falling a part. We took our kids. OMG i didn't even want them to touch anything.. Felt like we were gonna catch a disease there. The employees do not even care. So many people on drugs and even the workers look like it too. Do not go there! Do not take your kids!
BEST ACAI BOWLS AND SMOOTHIES!!! Seriously obsessed with this place and used to come at least 4 times a week when I lived in SB.

I'm a bit of an acai bowl snob, had some great ones - these are right up there. 

Usually a bit if a line and wait but only because these are legit.

Coffeebar Reno is a staple of my visit, multiple times whenever I'm in Reno.  
I love the location, on a quiet street with a couple tables outside.  The staff, they're all great.  The style of the shop is amazing - and their scones are some of the best I've had.  I love their latte's... can you tell, I'm in love with this place?
If you're in Reno - avoid the usual suspects (Starbucks, Peet's, etc) and give this local gem a try.  You will not be disappointed!

Ya learn something new everyday. Today I actually learned several things, all during my lunch at Bab Cafe!
First, I learned that Bab Cafe is owned by some experienced restaurant professionals. Jae runs the front of the house while JJ is in the kitchen. They're supported by an eager and passionate team of wonderful people who want to share their cuisine with you.
Their experience shows in everything at Bab Cafe, from the branded eco friendly sporks and bowls, to the design of the menu and restaurant, to the operation, service and overall guest experience. They are even so thoughtful to offer guidance on the amount of sauce they recommend for each menu item! It's all so well thought out and the final product is a great product and great guest experience. 
Today I also learned that Bab means rice.
Then I learned that Bibimbab means mixed rice! 
This whole time I'd thought Bibimbab was that Korean dish served in the hot clay pot with the crispy rice at the bottom! Turns out that's Torsol Bibimbab, a more formal version of the dishes they serve here!
Lastly I learned that Koreans don't consider it a meal if it doesn't have Bab aka rice! So while Bab Cafe is more than happy to accommodate all sorts of guest requests, including riceless bowls, they'd really request you try their bowls as they've designed them. 
Today we did just that, along with Korean style maki rolls (super tasty), japchae, house kimchi, and their Korean Fried Chicken Wings (Damn!!!) and I can't wait to go back!
Nice setting, authentic, delicious food. 2 stars for the service. We were seated & ignored for 10 minutes.

In many east Asian cultures, the craters and seas of the moon are interpreted as the image of a rabbit. Origin stories of this lunar leporid generally involve a theme of community, respect, and self-sacrifice. These allegorical traditions are the inspiration behind a once-a-month dinner served at the Moon Rabbit Cafe, a pay-what-you-can community effort staffed by volunteers at the Reno Buddhist Center (every third Saturday, 4pm-8pm).
Dining is done family style, with long tables of about 12 seats each and a total capacity of 80. We waited for roughly 30 minutes to be seated, and the staff tell me they served a record crowd of over 200 that evening. The aromas coming from the dining room were so enticing we didn't mind a bit on the wait, and the volunteer staff did a bang-up job keeping things friendly and feeling unrushed, all while moving folks through at a decent pace.
Each month a different theme is chosen, often with a guest chef creating the menu. April's theme was "Ooh La La Paris in the Spring", featuring some classic French dishes, each with a little twist showcasing the chef's creativity. First course was a canapé plate of crostini with toasted gruyere, a jam of caramelized onion and rosemary, garnished with fresh chives and chive blossoms. The appearance and flavor was akin to a deconstructed French onion soup, with a nice touch of garden freshness.
There were two entrées to choose from--one vegan, one not--both served with an arugula salad dressed in lemon and fennel seed vinaigrette. By itself the salad was a star on the plate, the peppery flavor of arugula pairing perfectly with the seasoned, slightly tart dressing. Layered ratatouille filled the vegan role, with green zucchini, yellow squash, and roma tomatoes. A thick, pureed sauce made from the vegetable ends, eggplant, red bell pepper, onion, lemon, rosemary, and oil perfectly bound it all together. Definitely one of the most flavorful squash-based dishes I've been served.
As if that wasn't enough, the chef's take on coq au vin started with chicken thighs marinated in pinot noir, seared in bacon fat, then braised in a blend of wine and housemade veggie stock. Combined with roasted red potatoes and turnips--and carrots sauteed in butter and cardamom--the resulting flavor profile was very well developed, subtle, and truly delicious.
Beverages included ice water, tea, coffee, and a spritzer that appeared to be a blend of concord grape juice and seltzer water. The spritzer didn't really work for me--reminding me of Kiddie Coolers my parents used to order for us tykes--but the coffee was quite good, very robust and a perfect pairing with dessert. Provided by a local bakery, dessert was a delicate little lemon and raspberry tartlet served a la mode. It featured a nice balance of tart and sweet, with a single whole raspberry right in the center. A perfect end to a great meal.
I found the pay-what-you-can concept a refreshing idea, allowing folks from all walks of life to enjoy a great meal together. Both while waiting to be seated and during the meal, it was hard not to connect and chat with perfect strangers enjoying the meal and the community vibe together. The next dinner is on May 21st, although the theme and chef are yet to be announced. The chef who prepared our delicious meal turns out to be a semi-amateur with a passion for cooking, and Moon Rabbit Cafe is seeking new chefs to create future dinners If you are or know someone with a similar drive to share your talents for a great cause, contact Shelly or Connie at 775-525-1182 or moonrabbit@renobuddhistcenter.org.

I was very pleasantly surprised when I tried the pho here. I had low expectations because I'm from the bay and Santa Barbara asian food can't compete with the bay. I got the rare steak pho and the steak was tender and good. The soup was flavorful, but not too salty either. I think I got a small size and it was a good portion because other places would usually give a tiny bowl. I wish they had a medium size but small was good. I would definitely come again, it really didn't disappoint as I thought it would!

I've gone here a couple times to eat but moreso for boba. I usually have a good experience at 101 Taiwanese Cuisine, however, this time has totally ruined my perspective of them. I ordered a avocado smoothie with my Uber eats order, added boba for $0.50 extra cents, but there was no boba to be found. This is completely unacceptable and since it was through uber eats I couldn't get it fixed. My review will remain at one star until I am compensated.

Great location and lots of places to sit (with outlets)! I would recommend this place for studying/working especially. Customer service was great, the barista was very friendly. The Nitro cold brew was absolutely fantastic (~$4.50). It wasn't too bold but it definitely had the coffee bean flavoring you know and love.

Fun, busy atmosphere. Always seems to buzz with activity. Espresso based drinks are good, but the drip coffee is pretty bad. It was probably a few hours old, in a hot pot, and when I asked for a fresh cup they gave the exact same old coffee again. Sad.

Stopped in for a croissant and iced latte with a couple other people. Great little cafe for relaxing outside, very dog friendly. Plenty of outdoor seating, although indoor seating is a bit limited and noisy during peak hours. Very long line when we went (Saturday morning) but it moved swiftly, so no complaints. 

The espresso had a wonderful, smooth flavor that was perfectly balanced and the croissant was buttery and flaky and everything was consumed quickly and happily. We will stop here the next time we are in the area! :)

Flew in from Brooklyn, NY the night before and was looking for a breakfast spot before starting our trip to Tahoe. 
We couldn't have been happier with our choice. Diner classics cooked to perfection! Everything was delicious and lovingly prepared. The service was exceptional, friendly, and welcoming. The restaurant itself was clean and tidy.
This is a gem with lots of small town charm. I'll be back the next time I'm in Reno...
Ordered off Uber eats. Excellent food. Fresh ingredients and healthy! Order the pork with rice and the #1. Will definitely order again and would recommend!

Love, love, love the whole milk lattes here... creamy, light and delicious. The service can be a little slow at times, but that latte makes it worth the wait. I have also enjoyed the lemon chiffon tea, and the barista said they make a latte with it as well. Their salads are good, the paninis are sometimes a little dry/bready (and I like bread ). The veggie quiche is too bland for me. But really, I go there for the latte!
Yummy, business trip in Reno for 3 days and we had dinner here twice. Chinese herb soup is my favorite, real nice Chinese soup.
Wow! So happy to have found this gem while I was getting my car repaired. The owner is the nicest and the veggie sandwich was superb. So fresh and delicious!

Just about the only "bad" thing I can say about this place is that the seating is always scarce! That says a lot about their business...the coffee bar is an awesome place. Great location, great service, awesome coffee...very relaxing spot. I'm not a huge coffee person, but this is one of my top coffee spots in Reno. Love it.

Love love love this place. At first I was taken aback on the price but worth every penny and it was a LOT of food. 
I got the spicy pork BimBop and a side of kimchi. Highly recommend.

We found this place to be fairly disappointing. Maybe we just ordered the wrong stuff? There were several different breakfast sandwiches on the menu. We were looking for just a quick bit. Simple pastries, donuts etc. The place calls itself a bakery, so I assumed the croissants, pastries, and donuts would be very fresh. This was not the case. I had a ham & cheese croissant, which was ok, but not that fresh, flakey etc. My daughter ordered the "seasonal donut" which was $4.00. It was just an iced cake donut with colored sprinkles. Nothing more than you'd find at a cheap donut place for $1.00 or less. My wife had a blueberry danish. Again, it was OK, but not great. This place says it is a bakery. Am I wrong for assuming the baked goods would be fresh and better than average? If you're going to charge me $4.00 for a donut, it better be the best darn donut I ever ate. Next time we're in town, we'll try somewhere else.
Love this place! Staff is always friendly when I come! Their matcha latte is so good too!

I usually love keva juice but I just went there today and I am very unsatisfied with their customer service. Emilee "helped" me and seemed to be rushing me the entire time I was there. I asked her option on a drink and she just seemed to rush me on a choice instead of giving an honest option. Then I tried switching my medium to a small, because their prices a bit ridiculous, she tried to say no to me getti g a smaller drink because they already started it. I'm sorry but that is because you rush your orders and customers, I didn't even pay yet. I dont know I just feel all these places hire kids and dont train them on how to give great customer service. I come to smoothie and coffee shops to take a break from my hero. And rushed day not to feel like I'm on the clock myself.

BEST HIDDEN LOCAL BURGER SPOT. For over 10 years, I have been coming here! Perfect place to come after surfing/swimming/craving a good a** burger! 
Best:
The delicious burger ofcourse with cheese and avocado !!
The good:
Presentation isn't the best but it doesn't matter when the food is so delicious . Only the locals really now about the secret spot 
The bad:
The fries are cooked fresh but just need additional salt.
It's a bit of a drive coming from downtown, only has one location; however very much worth the drive! They NEED to open another location!

Used to go here back when I went to UCSB and had the mad munchies :)
I've only had the char bugers, fries, and zucchini sticks, so this review is only for those. They're pretty decent, especially if you're too lazy to cook a burger or fries, or don't know where to even buy zucchini. lol.
They have a burger special (forgot what day), try it then...

The food is good and the service is fast. Would be a great take out lunch or dinner. Great way to introduce yourself to Korean food in a fast and casual setting. The kimchi was great and the bulgogi bowl delicious. I will eat there again and you should try it. Why only 4 stars then? First, $2 for a tiny, half-filled cup of kimchi is rediculous when bowls are already $9-12 and a drink is $2+. It's ok to charge for kimchi, but the size needs to increase. Second, the water cups are tiny. How do you expect someone to eat in without having to get up and fill a cup a million times? Ruins the eat-in dining experience, even for a casual, healthy food fast place.

Just had their 1.89 charburger sunday special. added cheese, avo, and jalepeno. very tasty. 
this may be our new neighborhood go-to place for when we want some good food fast and cheap. 
bf had the bbq chicken sandwich which was very good too.
I also got an order of zucchini stix - yum.  
cant wait to try the rest of the menu!
Love this place!!! Awesome, fun, clean atmosphere. The staff are super friendly and the drinks are AMAZING!! Yum Yum!!
Awesome new place with a nice vibe inside. I loved the foghorn waffles - a unique and delicious spin on chicken and waffles. Coffee was great and service was good.

This is my favorite coffee shop in Reno for a work/business meeting. The staff are amazing, before you order your drink they'll walk you through recommendations patiently figuring out what you're in the mood for. Currently I'm on a "warm decaf drink without a lot of sugar" kick so it's taking me a minute to order and the staff at Swill are ever so kind and helpful. Once you order and your drink is made they'll bring it to your table instead of calling you up. Simply pleasure, but ever-so-meaningful. If you order a pot of tea they'll check on it while you're there, make sure it isn't steeping too long, etc. Its these little things that make this place 100% for service. They also have smoothies and baked goods. I recently tried a slice of chocolate pumpkin loaf and it was exquisite. 

I'm yet to mention my favorite thing about this place. The tables! There is an adjunct room full of spacious collaboration tables and comfortable seating areas. Unlike typical coffee shops, it's away from the counter so it's quite enough to conduct business without grinders or other load coffee-making-noise that you have to talk over. There are a ton of tables and the place is never packed so whenever I have to meet with groups of people (if I have the time to drive to this part of town) I prefer to meet here. Another plus, there's always plenty of parking.
Great food. Very fresh and organic. Great service.  Great atmosphere. Loved everything about it. Highly recommended.
Came here 4 years ago during vacation. We came back but nothing change after years . The foods were still as good as before and the service were great too.

If you are from a bigger city like LA or NYC and are craving some more tasty/authentic Vietnamese food, look no further. Sip of Saigon not only has fantastic food (and plenty of options for vegetarian folks like myself), the coffee is BOMB and the atmosphere is adorable. Highly recommend the Bahn Mi, the tofu is fantastic!

Giant chunks of açaí throughout that missed the blades of the blender. Vibe was less than desirable. The wait was long. Disappointed to say the least. All 3 of us threw away more than half of the bowls.

The food is tasty, I'll give them that. But when one buys a $9 cup of soup, to be you need to purchase a half baguette if you want a piece of bread with the soup because they are low on bread is absolutely ludicrous.
Great breakfast place! Everything is delicious and the staff are great! Highly recommend!! The fresh squeezed juice is amazing
poke is my favorite food and i was so bummed that there weren't any GOOD poke places in iv:( but now i can happily say that i will be spending all my money at this place. phenomenal.
Food was excellent and the service was even better!! Will definitely be back soon!!

My server Nick and Chris were by far the most amazing people. Not only was the food sublime but the service I had received was humbling. These two servers have inspired me to become a better person and ensure that the world is made a better place one belly at a time

Eggs benny: 10/10. Almond milk iced coffee 10/10. Outdoor seating *chefs kiss*
Staff? AMAZING
Please give this little spot a try. It was a pleasant experience and great breakfast food.

OH MY GOD this place is absolutely amazing and incredible and delicious. I can't believe there's a place like this in Reno. I'm shook and appalled it's absolutely sensational I LOVE LOVE LOVE the Taiwanese spaghetti is a must, I love the beef and pork wrapped pancake, POPCORN CHICKEN IS SOOOOOO GOOD, and the milk teas were incredible. I wish I had this Taiwanese place back at home wow. 10/10 would recommend.

One of the best huevos rancheros I've ever had.
The coffee was good too! Friendly service. I will definitely  come back when come back to Santa Barbara.
I was pretty impressed with how good the rice bowl was. I couldn't finish it all, the cup of broth was delicious and refreshing!

Who would have thought that there would be good asian food in Reno. I ordered the beef noodle soup and was not disappointed. The broth was flavorful and meat was tender. The service was friendly and food came out fast and piping hot. They also have boba!

My 19-year-old niece and her friend visited us in Santa Barbara for one week, and knowing that the girls loved cats, I reserved time for a visit, and I am so glad I did.  The girls were delighted with the cats, as was I!  They're so cute.  And they're all different, both in looks and temperament.  They're identified by sex (pink collars for girls and blue collars for boys), as well as by temperament (beige collars for shy, and purple collars for unpredictable).  We sat and played with them, using the toys that were strewn about, and we even fed them with the treats that were provided.  Some of the cats were so active and entertaining, and very amusing.  A truly different kind of experience, and we wished that we could have taken one (or more) of the cats home with us.  Since the cats are taken from a shelter and provided with so much attention and care, we felt really good about supporting this type of endeavor.  We will, no doubt, return and possibly even adopt one of the cats!

Let's go for the pros :
The menu is widely ranged everything from Coffee and Tea , pastries , and lunch ideas. They even have a gelato bar.
My favorites to drink are always the Chai tea's , lavender latte , and their lattes in general but switch them out with coconut milk if you want to try something different. But overall I really enjoyed their different tea lattes.
The food is well thought out and there's always something different but you can always count on some staples as well. Their pastries are enjoyable , not necessarily the best out there but still really good. I have yet to have any of their gelato but it really does look yummy. Their sandwiches are very good as well.
The parking is decent. There is a small parking lot off to the side and then if that's full there's street parking but there's always plenty of spaces. Their hours are very reasonable as well being that they are open till about 9 p.m. or so in the evening.
Just a couple cons :
Definitely do not go at rush hour you will not have any place to sit or you'll be standing inside during winter hours to waiting for a place to sit. I would recommend to go either mid morning or later in the afternoon.
One thing I was highly disappointed in were there crepes , definitely not authentic at all.
Their prices are hit-and-miss for me. I don't mind paying extra for local places but I expect more from the food in general. The pricing on the drinks are very reasonable.

Such outstanding service!!! The coffee is incredible. Love the vibe, welcoming locals and visitors alike. Great ambiance, casual and airy. Thank you for the recommendations and the outstanding cold brew!!! Can't wait to return. Excited to add to my craft coffee mug collection too!
Very pleasantly surprised about authenticity of the food right in downtown Reno. Happy we made the drive from Truckee to try it out!
Love this place and the service has become excellent. Best place for breakfast or lunch, imho.

Highly recommended if you're into Açaí bowls. The fruit was very fresh and delicious. The portions were huge and the granola was tasty. The one we ordered had coconut shavings on top. I don't like coconut, but I ate every bit of it.
Best tortas in town, they are huge and yummy! Would definitely order from here again! Love the portion of fries they give with your combo and they have great customer service

Breakfast has a fantastic atmosphere, one that is perfect for a traveling freelancer or local surf bum. The staff is friendly and the coffee is strong! I especially fancy the vegan chocolate chip tahini cookie dipped in a cupa black coffee.
Very authentic Korean bibimbap. Try Kimchi bokeumbap and spicy pork bibimbap. Food here made you satisfying your hunger after losing all your money for slots.

Always good service!! I like to get a bunch of small plates to share and the prices are more than fair. So delicious and fresh. The decor is beautiful and the restaurant is clean. One of my favorite date-night spots.
Oh my gosh almond milk latte- amazing! And the service was spectacular, so friendly!!

We eat here once in a great while because its near our house and the food is good. They have a great space but I don't feel that they take maximum advantage of it. Doesn't feel cozy or charming and that is also reflected in their employees. It's too bad because if those minus points were fixed we'd spend more money there even tho it's way overpriced.
Amazing coffee, amazing food menu (for a coffee house), and just a great vibe/ambiance inside and out!

It's strange when food is inconsistent when it's old ladies who their entire lives made this food makes it funny.  I visited this place a handful of times when in town and the food that was always inconsistent was the rice and beans.  Of all things!  One time the rice was too cuminy.  Other times bland.  Other times just right.  What's going on?
I am addicted to their tostada.  I ask for rice on the tostada because it's only chicken and beans.  
Their cheese enchiladas have onion pieces in it and my husband orders it without.
The cheese enchilada is delicious.  It's simple but I say we like it a lot because of the good cheese they use.
I also love their beef tacos--they have potatoes mixed in.  And the shell is the home-fried poofy kind and not the generic taco shells.  
The downside is for their bowl of chips and salsa, their chips are always stale.  That's a huge disappointment.  But  I guess their salsa makes up for it because I use that for my food.  
Service also I have to say is a downside when there aren't a lot of people in there.  You'd think they'd give you better service but it was the exact opposite.  The waitress ignored us most of the time to the point where I had to get up and ask for things because she either forgot or is very very slow (because she preferred counting her money).

Waited 40 minutes for food... requested a refund. I have eaten here many times... people were asking where their food was, overheard two complaints about wrong food being delivered. As We requested a refund we were told that our food was being plated. There were customers outside that ordered, prior to our order being placed that had not received food. I've been there during hustle and bustle of food service on a busy weekend. Today's experience was unacceptable, and a waste of time. There was plenty of staff in restaurant and kitchen. 
The thing that was the most unacceptable to me was the dog in the restaurant. None of the staff asked if it was a service animal. In attached picture you can see posted on the wall notification from Santa Barbara County Health Inspector, No Animals Allowed!
Went in with a hundred dollar bill and they wouldnt let me get anything.. Terrible service I was starving while watching my friends eat absolutely pathetic and ridicilous

Everything over here is good, but I don't get the hype that it gets. There's always a wait, and it's always the first place my friends' suggest whenever we go out for brunch. Don't get me wrong it's okay. It's might even be pretty good, but when I'm coming up to visit I want something to really hit the spot. Cajun Kitchen just doesn't do it for me. I think I enjoyed this place waaayyyy more when I was still living in Goleta. Now I only get to visit a few times a year. I have so many places that I absolutely love in the Santa Barbara area that going here is pretty far down on my list.

With that said, the biscuits and the cornbread are both phenomenal. Both sides come with apple butter and butter. Those have always been great and are almost worth the wait to get a table. On my last trip here, the cornbread with apple butter were eyes rolling to the back of my head good. And then I went on to eat my California Benedict and was sad that I had started with the cornbread. It wasn't bad. It was okay. But it was like having such a strong start with such a weak finish. The hash browns are good but I wouldn't recommend the home fries. The jambalaya with eggs is decent but I think that's because I really like the eggs mixed in. 

The service here is also usually very good. They're usually really nice and very attentive. On my last visit, I think our server was just having a bad day and he seemed like he really didn't want to be there. 

Overall if you live in the area and want to get brunch then go for it. If you have friends visiting, go ahead and toss it up as a possible place for brunch. My three stars doesn't mean that I don't like it. It just means that I think it's fine. It's over hyped but fine.

- BYOR (bring your own rice). Like a few of the other Asian restaurants around Reno rice doesn't automatically come with entree. It is an up charge to get a small bowl of rice that should already be included with the entree. 
- good to great food 
- good service 
- parking could be tricky 
- fair prices

A gem in Reno. First, the food --- the pot roast meal box. That braised pork rice is so delish. And that's just a side. The pot roast itself so flavorful and tender. The pickled vegetables added a nice touch to change the palate. The restaurant itself is modern, Asian (not to be obvious). Overall, it was a pleasant surprise.
Great breakfast place. We went on a Sunday and there was a line but I thought the food arrived in a decent amount of time. Staff was very friendly.   They have indoor and outdoor seating.

This place definitely feels like it belongs in Italy. It has a limited yet delicious espresso menu; I usually stick with a cappuccino or mocha, and both are just right (so much better than Starbucks). They also have the display case with several sandwiches with Italian names. I haven't tried too many of these because they look really big. They apparently import some stuff from Wild Garlic next door, like their calzones.
But my favourite food item here is the veggie frittata. Best frittata ever, and  perfect for a light lunch. This place is almost always crowded, but I've never had a problem finding seating or parking. I do feel sorry for the nearby residents though, as they get a lot of Coffeebar customers parking in front of their house.
Lastly, and I noticed this with their Truckee location too, they use dry noodles as stir sticks, which I think is a great idea- not only are they biodegradable, but edible too! I like to dunk mine in my coffee and nibble on it (though I don't recommend this for people with sensitive teeth).

Fun place. Good food. 
I had the eggs Benedict which is not on their menu board but they do make it. It's excellent. 
The hash with salmon is also good. 
They also have sandwiches and burgers.

I love this place so much! All the baristas are so nice, and the atmosphere is wonderful. I'm inspired to do great work while surrounded by impressive art on the walls and  great coffee in my hand. I discovered it only about a week before the lockdown, and I can't wait to go back and try a few of their other offerings and maybe catch some live music.

Two times I have been in, and two times I have been very impressed. The service has been thoughtful and very knowledgable, and my espresso shots were wonderful each time. You can tell that the barista knows his beans and machines very well. Also, the machines! Have you seen these things? They're great. Go by, say hi. Buy some beans, because they're super solid too.

Trying the chai.   Best ever even compared to the places in Santa Cruz!  The chai is the closest to what I've had in India.  No additional ingredients needed.  Looking forward to the sausage burrito!  Yeah.
I felt totally unwelcome when I first walked in! Then the front counter lady's were to bizzy talking about god knows what ! Finally got to make an order! The food was fine ! Passeble

TL;DR: Don't get the matcha latte. Everything else was amazing!

This place was so cute so I had to visit! I loved all the art around the space and the people there was super nice. I initially got the matcha latte with almond milk but honestly, it was not good. I don't know if it was the powder but it tasted very watery so I got a drip coffee and as suspected, it was fantastic! The beans are from Portland and you just can't go wrong with coffee!

Why open only until 3pm "due to Covid" after over a year? This business is missing out on after-work business. I was so disappointed when I came here to order Easter goodies last week... and the bold sign out front still says open until 5:30pm on weekdays.
