Arrive as close to opening time as possible.  This place fills up, and every time we go, the Mrs. and I are the only non-Asians there.  Everything we've had has been a pleasure.  Every trip there reminds me of when I lived in central Taiwan.  The Taiwanese bento boxes are especially authentic.  I am looking forward to taking the plunge with their beef tendon stew, something I especially associate with Taiwan.

I LOVE the Nook Cafe. The Cobb salad is huge, the burgers are great, the Club Sandwhich is awesome and the open-face turkey sandwich is to die for. The Nook is the perfect little hole in the wall breakfast or lunch place for those times when you can't figure out what to eat for breakfast or lunch. Now that I'm back working around the corner from them I eat there once or twice a week. 
Situated behind the Rainbow Market I usually pull in using the driveway for Long John SIlvers... pull in and a straight shot back, on the left. 
The staff is friendly, the food is good, and the service is quick if you only have a short time for lunch. 
Do yourself a favor and try the Nook, you won't be disappointed.
Good to find a Taiwanese place in Reno. Great food and good price, various flavored drinks~

By far the best coffee place out there.
Beats Starbucks hand down.
And inexpensive compared to Starbucks 
Tried their Dream Weaver and Americano, OMG...
THEY WERE TO DIE FOR.
Definitely my new favorite coffee place. 
The staff was awesome and very informative, since I had never been there and they answered my questions on what certain things were.

It was just okay..for something quick and easy it'll do but not the best korean food...on the bland side.  I like Hana garden much better but they are super slow.  The place is small but clean cuz it's new and the people working there are really nice...but the food was just okay to me and I got at least 5 different things to try out.

I sent my boyfriend in to get me a breakfast bagel since I have been super sick. Even though this place is right down the street we don't ever think to come here. They definitely sold me, because the breakfast sandwich was delicious! It takes a little time to prepare since they make it fresh, but well worth the wait. I definitely recommend the cheddar bagel! We were lucky we got the last two cheddar bagels! My boyfriend said the owner was very friendly and that he just recently took ownership of the business. The truth is I like their breakfast sandwich better than Wet Hen's and it's closer. Can't wait to try their coffee!

I actually can't comment on the food - I was so turned off by the place I left without ordering. When I went there today, I had to drive back and forth 3 times before I could find a parking space. When you get inside, there's a tiny sign on the cash register that tells you where there is a parking lot, but you still have to ask where it is. I wasn't even sure I could find anywhere for myself or the 2 people with me could sit - we managed to grab the last spot while we looked at menus - if we waited, it would have been gone and we would have been eating at the counter, I guess, since the staff wasn't even paying attention to how much seating there was and just kept taking orders.  I went to stand in line to order. While I was in line (next up to order) some people walked up and stood on the other side of the person ordering while I was standing there waiting - and the staff began taking their order, ignoring me. In short, no place to park your car or your butt and the staff seriously needs to pay attention. Won't be going back.

I love the menu,but im a local an i been here many times and there is never a good satisfying  good welcome or would u like to oreder!! Nothing not even a hi! Just a straight face!! Love love the items on the menu!!! But costumers service sucks !!!    
 Worst part!!! When i ask for a container to go! The cashier did not even bother to strive to make up for the straight face! Without a word she just pointed at the to go containers!!!!
Fresh, tasty and generous breakfast burritos served with a heaping side of kindness! Heartily recommend.

Tried coffee bean for the first time today and it was by far the worst coffee I've had in years. The latte was essentially hot milk even though I requested a double shot. If you happen to accidentally stumble in just ask for steamed milk, it's the same as their lattes at half the price. Please go anywhere else to enjoy coffee, literally anywhere.

Simple bar foods but amazing quality. Happy hour is done the right way here.
The wings are amazing. Get the bruschetta bread. Tots are good. But mainly wings is your best bet. 
Happy hour 4-6. Great food for a great price.

Take a break from the wine and incredible restaurant for the Natural. Don't think "healthy" food can't be satisfying. Great protein smithies, and the flavors here (some Asian, some Latin) are amazing. Huge portions. Perfect for lunch. Chicken is a must here, on whatever dish.

I'm a black coffee drinker, and I've never had a bad cup at Swill. I ordered a specialty drink once and was not terribly impressed, mainly because I felt the guy behind the counter wearing the newsie cap was less than friendly and understanding regarding my order. I guess my Mexican mocha, which I asked to be made with half coffee and half steamed milk to reduce the sweetness of the drink was more difficult to understand than a iced, half caff, ristretto, venti, 4-Pump, Sugar Free, Cinnamon, Dolce Soy Skinny Latte

After that experience I felt like I needed a beer or a glass of wine, which they serve there too! 

But that aside, Swill is a great place to hang. They have the most workspace of any coffee shop in town, making them a great spot to meet with friends, a small organization, or even host an event. I regularly visit Swill for the 1 Million Cups presentations every Wednesday from 9-10am. Local startups and entrepreneurs present their ideas to the group for feedback on a wide range of business topics. 

The owner has done a lot to get involved with and support the local community, and she's done a great job of creating a cozy and comfortable space, including displaying local artists on the walls. If you haven't been before, you should certainly give them a shot (PUN INTENDED).
Cal Taco has been consistently awesome for the past 10+ years I've been a regular there.

We were sick of eating buffet and thinking why not try out some local restaurants. We ordered a fried rice, chow mein, pork chop over rice and popcorn chicken. Overall, the food were pretty good but the portion were kinda small.

Great job on the food improvements guys!!!  Others must think so too. See you have moved up in ratings. That's what it takes. Great to see you doing well. We had a great dinner there a month ago. Much improved. Keep it up
Update- wow. What happened. Back again but the brunch Sunday was not what I expected.  Room half full but told had to wait. Limited staff on it seemed.  Food def not up to par with last dinner. 
Host was not good. 
Out of 6 people no one liked food.

OMG, disappointing brunch trip this past weekend.  First of all, I probably did not do my homework and wanted to try out their Vegan Chef menu options.  Those items are only served on the dinner menu.
My husband and I had brunch and I had Colin's special with chicken, eggs whites, vegetables.  I rea lize that's this is the furthest from vegan but it sounded pretty good.  It looked fantastic but the chicken was very dry.
My husband had steak and eggs.  Something was wrong with the steak as it had a funny smell.  It looked fantastic though.  Unfortunately, we had to complain to the manager about the steak and luckily it was written off the check.
I know for a fact that this restaurant does better.  Maybe it was due to the fact that there was a convention in the hotel and they were super busy.  I have sampled Roundabout's items at various events and have enjoyed their food.  I will give it another try, hopefully before vegan chef is over because I really wanted to try those options.
The fried rice and pho are really delicious. The people who work there are also nice.

Well i wasnt even gonna give em 1 star..because i was just here a couple mins ago..i order a wonton soup but after mixing it i found out that there's like 4 or 5 small insects in my soup!!!so i called the server and told them that my souo had an insects in it..and she goes " oh would you like us to make you a new one???? I was like no thank you i dont want anymore of that soup..so after that im expecting them to ask me if i want something else!!! But then the lady server just turn her back on me and ignore me the whole time i was there!. So i was so pissed and just left..its very poor service and im not going back i this resto ever...

I ordered delivery and the food was over all fine. The prices however are kind of crazy. A bag of chips was $3.50. Honestly at that point I should have just gone to Los Agaves where they give them to you for free with the meal.

Just ordered the curry w/ rice and found metal from what looks like a kitchen scrubber in my food. Wondering how it got there. Lost my appetite. This is also a safety hazard as the metal is quite sharp.
Excellent endroit pour un petit déjeuner vitaminé... fruits et oat-meal à l'honneur .... je recommande vivement. Pour le café et le thé, il y a le Santa Barbara coffee à deux portes.

The Natural Cafe is a great casual restaurant with lots of healthy and sustainably sourced options. My favorite is the Hungry Planet Burger™. In my opinion, this is one of the best vegetarian burgers out there. The taste and texture are delicious and on par with the Impossible Burger, another of my favorites. It'll come with a side of corn chips and tasty salsa.
I also have to mention their desserts. I've had the carrot cake and lemon bars, and while I favor the cake, both a great options for sweet treats after your meal.

Josef's Has been here for years. And I have been coming here for years. They probably make the best bread in town.   I have noticed lately however it's getting pretty shabby. Need some repair and some cleaning. It used to be like a European café. Now it's beginning to look like a greasy spoon. Not to much wrong with that is I have had some of the best food I've ever eaten in a greasy spoon. But Josefs should be more than that.
I tried 3 different places while staying in the area and this one hands down the best. The coffee is delicious, I highly recommend one of the pour overs, it hit the spot.

Options aplenty to please our group-- a picky kid, a vegetarian, someone in the middle of a Whole30, and an eggs, bacon, potatoes, toast breakfast traditionalist. Food was tasty and service was attentive but not in your face. Everyone enjoyed their food-- two build your own hashes, a breakfast burrito, eggs and pancakes, and the afore mentioned traditional brekkie. Herb aioli was a high point! Would definitely return.

Now I realize why there are no reviews from 2016 - it is NO LONGER OPEN TO THE PUBLIC. 
The folks working in the lobby were super friendly in explaining that their corporate offices decided to close it to the public a few months ago.
Love their coffee, I wish there was one in santa Maria

The signs say "Blue Whale"; I think "Nameless" is the new branding that isn't up yet.
That said, the coffee was delicious and the scone was delightful. Good stuff.

Came here looking for a healthy alternative and left very happy! 
I ordered the peanut butter chocolate smoothie with protein and boy was I happy! Their variety of smoothies and types of bowls are endless here! Made Jamba Juice almost look like fools! They have 3 different sizes you can choose from and the medium is a happy medium to being full and using it as a dessert!
I'll be back to try their whole menu and the service was great and friendly!

God I just love this place. First of all, the halloween/occult/spooky theme is everything I could ever want in a coffee shop. I've never seen another cafe with the same theme, and they do it so well. Second, their espresso is so good. It has such an amazing flavor profile, so many coffee shops have espresso that falls flat on the tongue, but superstitions is a different story. I get all of my lattes with oat milk and usually add an extra shot, so the total for my drinks comes to around eight dollars, which is fine but no doubt expensive for a coffee. BUT it's worth it! Also they have the most creative drinks I have ever seen in a café, and I go to a lot of cafés.  They release a bunch of creative themed drinks for different holidays as well. I loved the "lovers latte" from Valentine's Day.  Also the crew is super nice. if you're thinking about going to superstitions just get in your car and go, no think.

This was the first time I've ever tried Taiwanese food. It was pretty interesting but I tried most of the stuff before. The bubble tea wasn't too bad. They put powder for the flavoring and I 'chewed' most of the powder. The tea didn't have to much flavor or tea flavor. I give the tea 3 stars. I really liked the sweet sausage fried rice. It had a decent amount of chopped up sausage, little carrot cubes, and peas. I give the sweet sausage 4.5 stars. If you are staying in Reno around Silver Legacy you can probably walk to here. I recommend this restaurant because it's a 5-10 minute walk from the hotels and they have some good food but I can't say all of it is good food because I haven't tried it.

Open the walk up window already.  
This is ridiculous.  
Good coffee but it's time to open the walk up.  Let's get back to living.

Maybe not my favorite breakfast spot, but their breads are top notch. Maybe even the best bread in town :3 
Staff is very cute, I mean friendly!

We enjoy 101 Taiwanese Cuisine.  Seating is limited which can make it hard to get in on Friday and Saturday nights but worth the wait.  Prices are reasonable and portions are huge, always have leftovers.  They have TV screens that show various meals, really neat and helpful to see various dishes.

This is one of my favorite stops in Reno, for the coffee, the food and the atmosphere as well.
Great coffees, pastries, breakfast items and more, a nice wine selection and both inside and outside it seems Coffeebar is always full. My go-to drink is their chocolate cappuccino 
I use this as a remote work location where I can enjoy the coffee while working. Yes it can get noisy but a quiet workspace drives me nuts!
So yeah, this place lives up to all the yelp hype. Super tasty and I was able to get my coffee fix next door while I waited for my bowl. Going back the next two days I'm in here town it's that good.
What a treasure...fantastic food, super super kind & attentive service, homemade jam, soooooo good!
I was not there but my partner s has been there twice already for the past two weeks for business meetings and he says the service is fantastic and the coffee is good

Had a beef noodle soup and the beef was almost inedible. Meet was a horrible cut and hard to chew. Probably was the worst beef noodle soup I ever had. I walked in at a later time of the day so not sure if the quality would be better had I come earlier.

Velvety espresso pull, great taste. A little low on the crema. Offered flat water instead of sparkling for the tasting, but still worked well.
The vanilla latte was excellent! Not too sweet, coffee taste was deep. Go-to any time I'm here now.
As with all good coffee spots, lots of hipsters, but hey it's good company.

Backyard bowls is a gem of Santa Barbara. Every single time I am in one the staff treats me so well and is so nice a friendly. I've never had a bad meal here. I would suggest anyone visiting to go here for some great breakfast! Stay woke.

Visited this place during the July 4th week for breakfast. The location isn't the easiest place to spot and we actually past it up while walking since it's right near the walkway under 101 HWY.  Just remember it's next door to Casa Blanca (the white building).  We ordered the hash plate, luau french toast and organic oatmeal.  The food was very good although the corn beef was a bit stringy and not cut up in smaller pieces.  Service and workers were friendly and helpful.  We will definitely be back again when visiting SB.

I've been here a few times and decided to bring my mom for her first visit. I usually always get the hash but this time I tried the kale and quinoa salad (although it ended up being spinach and brown rice by the time I got it). It was very good although they were a little heavy handed with the dressing for my liking. My mom tried the hash with the sweet potatoes and veggie patty. We both really enjoyed the combination and she especially liked the toast and jam. 
Overall, I'd say that the food is tasty and consistent, a place I definitely think adds some flavor to SB's breakfast/brunch scene.

Expensive but worth the occasional splurge. The backyard bowl is big enough to share if you aren't too hungry. I enjoyed every single ingredient:  acai, banana, strawberry, hemp milk, blueberries, goji berries, bee pollen, granola, and honey. I will definitely come back to try other items when I'm next in town.
All of our meals were excellent. Spaghetti squash hanger steak butter nut squash soup flat bread pizza. Yum Yum Yum

A bit expensive, but I was quite happy with my food. I've been here twice, the second time I brought my sister. The hot and sour soup was different from what I'm used to, but I really enjoyed it. Their boba is good, too. The servers I've had were nice enough and made sure I was happy with my meal. 
All in all, I'd definitely go here again if I ever end up spending time in Reno.

I LOVE THIS PLACE! Whether your are counting your macros, have special dietary needs, or just want some fresh food, BFF Cafe has something for everyone. Their specialty are "zoodles" which are spiralized zucchini with protein and sauces added. My favorite so far is "The Hunter" which is braised beef, zoodles, broccoli l, red potato, and chimichurri sauce. If you're in a hurry and want something on the go they have fuel packs to pick up and enjoy later. They also have protein shakes, protein coffees, and overnight oats you can pull out of their fridge display. I have eaten here quite a few times and the staff is always knowledgable and friendly. The gluten free cookies are also a delicious guilt free treat!

Excellent experience. Casual dining, high quality food with excellent service. I had the beef chilaquiles special. It was one of the best chilaquiles dishes I've ever had. I also enjoyed the gluten free pancake. My wife had the avocado toast which she loved and my daughter had the French toast (ate all of it). And the coffee is excellent!

I have been increasingly impressed by the food. While I have yet to go and like everything I've ordered I've consistently tried new dishes and loved a majority. Last time we had the spicy basil chicken, which was very tasty and I love the tons of roast garlic in it, the meat so dry that I shredded it and gave it to my dog. But besides that mishap we also had the spicy eggplant with pork (vinegary, tender, and tasty) and the beef chow fun. The beef chow fun was different in the sense that it was more saucy than your traditional dried fried, but it was super good, great flavors. They don't serve the stinky tofu anymore much to my dismay, but I suppose it's a general hard sell for most people. I love the won ton soup although the number of won tons you get is variable at best, but it's so comforting to eat. I like the food a lot but I would steer clear of the boba, they currently can't seem to get the consistency right.  I'll be definitely going back for more food and maybe one of those days I'll be feeling up to the challenge of trying the boba again.

Ambiance: casual,beachy, out door seating ,order at the cash register, find your own seat, get your own water...however the food is not typical for these scene
Service: friendly
Food: Fresh, homemade & tasty, freshly squeezed orange juice is given thumbs up by my son who doesn't like orange juice
Price: $80 for breakfast for family 5 a bit pricier than expected.
Our first stop in Santa Barbara and I'm so glad we chose this spot for lunch. Delicious and filling! Definitely substitute the local granola for the granola the bowls come with

The girls working here were cute,  everything else was sub par, Drinks were not well mixed,  wine list out of date,  and the food ranged from average to unacceptable. Service was good and the staff tried hard to compensate for all the other failings. We will never go back.
Josef's does an incredible job! The food is good, reliably so. The coffee also. There is a great selection of pastries and breads and the staff is friendly and nice.
Food here was amazing.  I was told the cook was a 65 year old man. I was so impressed with favor.  Customer service was get.  Attentive at all times.  Looking forward to our next visit
This is in my opinion the consistently best dirty chai in town. Reasonable prices and always friendly staff. Forget the trendy places! Worth the walk here.
Just had the BEST Tomato Bisque soup I've ever had.  Relaxed and Cozy atmosphere.  Love this place

- THE FOOD
The worst McDonald's I've ever had. The fries were absolutely the nastiest. Usually, I would feel terrible after having 2 orders of fries, but nope, I felt the grossness hitting me after eating just ONE fry. The entire order of fries was intensely oily and greasy. There was no salt sprinkled on top whatsoever. The chicken nuggets were decent but all the sauces tasted really off and bitter. The spicy McChicken left me completely unsatisfied as it was not spicy at all. There was also way too much mayo in there.  
- THE ENVIRONMENT
Probably the dirtiest McD that exists. Upon entering, you get hit by a huge whiff of body odor, urine, grease, and weed. The place is clearly run down and is in a major need of a face lift. The tables and floors are nasty and sticky. I wouldn't even take $100 to just sit there and eat.

This is by far my favorite coffee shop on State St. It truly baffles me that people claim to enjoy locally owned coffee shops, yet complain when they do not have access to luxuries that places like Starbucks offer. I work on the same block as Good Cup so I am there literally everyday. And for someone to complain about capped electricity sockets is crazy. The buildings attached to the Metro building are old and capping electric sockets is simply a safety precaution. And after the multiple power outages that the 900 block has experienced the past nine months, almost all the buildings on that block have done the same thing. Good Cup is the kind of place that unfortunately very few appreciate. Point of the matter - the coffee is good, service is great. Just go.

I ordered a last minute pumpkin pie for pick up the next morning, and it was not a problem for them.  The pie was ready when I showed up and delicious.  I had forgotten about this little gem, and when I walked in I wanted to buy all the treats they had on display - they were beautiful!  I think their pricing is beyond fair for their quality product.  
Just a heads up on the phone orders - you must pay over the phone, not when you pick up.

I love this place; it feels like home; The Beristas are wonderful; and if you want to study in this place for two hours nobody will say anything; plus they have specials every day; by the way high speed internet access is great. and every 10 times if you get a punched card your drink is free.

seems to have gotten worse lately, was served very old n hard crispy chicken pieces in their cheap pho baguettes.
Also got some cold shrimp served that were supposed to be deep-fried :/ They re-fried them so they got chewy and crispy, almost burnt. Not very delicious...

I've been here several times and I can honestly say that I absolutely love it.  I've tried several different coffees and have loved each one. I love how they have a regularly changing specialty menu. 
The most current coffee was a ginger latte. It came presented beautifully with a leaf design in the foam. Instantly your nose is greeted by the warm scent of ginger. Once you take a drink the ginger flavor is very smooth and extremely tasty!  You will instantly say mmm guaranteed.  
The atmosphere is relaxed, there is always interesting art to ponder and the staff is super friendly.  Stop in, grab some coffee and just sit and enjoy!
This place is my favorite Coffee shop in Santa Barbara. The atmosphere is very warm and welcoming. Also the coffees are always yummy. My favorite is Coconut Mocha!

On 35 minutes of waiting as of now. Wrong orders going out. No receipt was handed to me so I could even prove my order. It's a real cluster you know what in here.
I don't care how good this bowl will be (if I ever even get it).
Will not be back
Amazing latte.  lovely patio.  beautiful, neighborhood

I will never go back to this cat cafe- 
1.) it seems as though the cats there aren't the best to have in a place that advertises to people to pet and hangout with them- I reached out to lightly pet a cat on the head, and without notice, it attacked me and made me bleed. I've had cats my entire life and I was never in a situation like that before. There was also another cat that I suppose was new there and it was determined to start a fight with another cat by growling at it in the corner. I don't believe it is safe to come to this place, especially if you have a young child. 
2.) There is also a hefty price to get in that is questionable as to how much of it is actually donated to the animals.
This place is amazing. Food and staff are top notch. I would eat here everyday if I didn't live so far away. Even bought a local hotsauce. Will be stopping back next I'm in town.

It's a great start!  They haven't changed the inside of the place from the previous incarnations but it still looks great. 

The happy hour was nice. 25% off many bar menu items.  

My favorite was the cones.  Just the right offering to start a nice meal.  I enjoyed the poke as well.  Everything we had was good. 

I will be back for a deeper exploration of the dinner menu.  This was just an appetizer.

This is the best brunch place in SB!! I went here with my boyfriend, and we both built our own hashes. Mine was sweet potato, corned beef, spinach, corn, mushrooms, eggs, pepperjack cheese, and herb aioli. 
Everything was perfectly cooked. The corned beef was shredded beef. I loved that they put the cheese under the eggs so it could melt into the rest of the hash instead of only on the egg. Their multigrain toast is good, and they give you a light side salad. I thought the portion was good for the amount you paid for. It was a very satisfying meal! 
It's too bad about the location. It's kind of hard to see unless you're looking for it. It's right in between Casablanca and the SB Rock Gym, and the sign is behind some trees. Street parking was easy though :)

Ok is right, but doesn't offer same menu items on the Chinese menu as they do on the English menu, which made me a little pissed knowing what the dishes were and not being able to read Chinese :/
I saw plenty of what seemed to be locals or regulars ordering things that were definitely not on the English menu, one being oyster omelette, a Taiwan speciality.
Came twice during a quick weekend and found it random since there are not many Taiwanese restaurants around in general. One time was before the lunch rush and one was after. Was super excited but overall underwhelmed.
The restaurants "specialty" spicy basil chicken was not spicy at all. Both times I ordered spicy dishes and had to ask for more hot sauce. Chicken was inconsistently cooked and basil had no favor. Just very salty and heavy on the soy sauce.
Mocha boba drink had almost no mocha in it either. I got chocolate milk boba instead. Regular boba drink is decent.
Jia Jiang Mien was okay, again a little on the salty side and noodles were almost stale-tasting. Generous portion but can still make better at home.
Pork belly "burger" was a sad attempt on a food gimmick. The buns were stale, dry and crumbly or were in their freezer too long. Pork belly piece had fat all on one side. 
Everything else was just "okay" but not bad.
Would come back only for an incontrollable craving and I can't find anything else better!

I tried they're famous "The Elvis," and it was delicious...the first three bites. After that, I was kinda done. It's a little too rich but it is super yummy. 
If anything, definitely try their baked goods. Their breakfast was okay but their cinnamon roll was : crumbly, sweet, flaky, buttery. It was incredible. Wish I would have gotten some

I've only been here once but plan on coming back because I absolutely loved the mild braised beef noodles here.  I also had boba milk tea and it tasted just as great. I'd like to try the Thai tea the next time I go though. Yummmm.

This is just the kind of casual fast dining experience I was looking for.  Order at the counter, get your own drink, and find a seat for food delivery.  Fast, affordable, and tasty.  This isn't really a brunch spot where you sit and eat and drink slowly for a whole morning.  This is the kind of place you can grab a freshly cooked meal that's a bit out of the ordinary while enjoying people watching and then get on with your day.  I had a sweet breakfast with delicious fruits and nuts!  It really hit the spot before wandering State Street when it opened.  If you're looking for a slow brunch, keep scrolling.  If you're looking for a hearty breakfast, with a California flavor profile, make this your stop.

Deal Chicken has a thing right now where for $10 you can get $20 worth of food so I thought to try this. 
PROS:
- large menu good for any vegetarian or picky eater
- portions were large
- service was quick
- place was packed during the week at 4 (a good sign)
- food came with rice
CONS:
-parking, the lot is very narrow and I think there is room for maybe 8 cars in the lot which is shared with Starbuck's
- the sesame chicken has no sesame flavor (few seeds were on it)
- wouldn't hurt the woman at the register to smile
- while the entrees were reasonable, I thought the smoothies were overprices
-----------------------------------------------------------
Cheaper than Panda Express (STFU I love Panda), but a bit too far for me just to get Chinese fast food. While I would have no problem going back, I wouldn't make a special trip to come here.

I adore this place. It's cozy, has a nice aesthetic, and everybody here is very friendly! Even though I've only been here twice, I recommend the lavender latte, which is what I got the first time I came here. It's very light, floral, and it is a nice switch from a regular latte. I also tried the Paleo bowl today and I would recommend that as well. It's nice and flavorful, which is good if you're looking for something satisfying to have for lunch. 
Overall, I think that this is a great place to hang out with a couple of friends or to just have quality alone time!
The only downside I would say about this place is that it can get pretty crowded, which makes finding a seat inside difficult. But I do hear that the outdoor seating is quite nice. (:

This place is fabulous. Amazing burger with sweet potato  fries. They splitted the burger for us at no charge! We had their carrots, carrots, carrots appetizer, and it was very original and good.  The butterscotch dessert was so worth it. the ambiance is good, the staff is very friendly. Will come back!

I was very excited to try this place, but after having breakfast there, I would say it is way overrated. It would have been great if I can taste the coffee when drinking their cappuccinos, not just tons of milk. :(
Heaven in a bowl. Best acai bowl I've ever had.

I was disappointed in high price (low value), long wait time, and small portion size.
I ordered the "build a hash" with russet potatoes, pepper, onion, mushroom, corned beef, scrambled egg, roasted salsa at 10:13am. My friend got a very similar meal.
I was surprised to see that salad took up ~1/3 of the plate when it wasn't even mentioned on the menu board. Also, I was surprised that an orange juice cost $5 for ~10oz.
On the positive side, I liked the taste.
I didn't measure the wait time but it seemed to be ~15 minutes which seems long since it did not seem very busy/crowded.

cute, very "hipster", breakfast place.
The place is equal parts hipster, charming, and plain rundown. If the food was priced say...30% lower, the atmosphere would have been appropriate. However, it's too run down for $15 decent(not great) breakfast.  Fro $50 for breakfast for two, I expect cleanliness. 
Coffee with Rompope: 1/5: tasted like watered down budget instant coffee. definitely do not recommend.
Scramble: 3/5: overall taste of scramble was 4/5. However, they were refused to substitute egg whites for the scramble. I found that to be disappointing for a breakfast joint that prides itself for "made to order" food.  bacon was thick cut and good, biscuit was OK, fig jam was good. smashed potatoes were good, excellent fruit, coffee cake was meh. 
Dutch Baby: 3/5
Service: friendly but VERY SLOW for breakfast food. I get that it's made to order, but breakfast really shouldn't take more that 30 minutes, unless they're making biscuits and preserves from scratch upon ordering. If that's the case, then kudos.
They also do NOT have fresh squeezed OJ. I feel that's a must for a breakfast joint. 
Oh, and I swear I overheard the waitress pronounce beignets as "Beg-nay". I really hope she was joking because call me snotty, but I strongly believe a waitress should be able to properly pronounce all three items on the menu.

So defiantly by far the best coffee house In reno. Amazing customer service very friendly employees and an even better owner. If you are in town this is the best coffee I think you can get on the west coast. Very nice store. Good atmosphere and even bett

As someone who is not really a fan of breakfast foods (don't eat eggs and bacon or sausage), I loved this place.  I had their build-a-hash with veggies and vegetarian sausage, as well as the Hawaiian French Toast.  The place itself was fairly busy but still relaxed.

Had the Pho without noodles because I'm off da flour stuff. The broth was delicious! I had Pho in Vancouver last and this was so much better! Bummed I couldn't eat the noodles but super happy with the broth. I do wish the had more vegies to throw in since I couldn't get noodles it would have helped round out the meal since there was not alot more I could order. However, I'm on a special food plan so I will suggest people go when they are not so they can have the full food experience!

I don't understand how this place is rated as 1 $ in price. Dinner here will cost a single person about $20. I went alone last time and that's what my bill (including tip, probably) came out to. To get my fix of Viet food in IV, this is the place to go. But I've definitely experienced better and for cheaper.

The bowls are good but forget trying to go there if you are in any sort of hurry.  I tried to call my order in over the phone several times only to have someone answer and immediately hang up.  After that the line went busy until I got there where I assume they just left the phone off the hook because they had a line.  I left without ordering when the girl in front of me was told there would be a 25 minute wait for her order.  Not great customer service, guys..  waste of a lunch break.

Swill Is one of the few independent shops in the southwest area of Reno.  It's regular espresso drinks like an Americano or drip coffee very gourmet and the atmosphere is very artistic and casual.  The seating inside is very comfortable and apparently they sell wine too.  If you are tired of Starbucks, come here.

I love this place. It's a great neighborhood gathering place for a yummy pastry and lavender latte. But this coffee bar is more than just coffee and treats.  Drop in for lunch and enjoy a paleo bowl or avocado toast or a series of other yummy home made meals. 

And don't forget a key word in their name ...bar. So it's a great place to meet up with friends after a long day. 

There is plenty of seating for Two and larger tables when you're meeting a group of friends.  There is one bathroom so we all know how that can look lol.  There is both street and lot parking   The staff is friendly and ready to whip up some new twist on a traditional latte. 

Stop by and enjoy !
Delicious food. Great service and food. They have a great avocado toast.it a beautiful restaurant

Just your normal average coffee/tea shop...except this one has no power outlets. At all. Which I guess makes it not your normal average coffee/tea shop at all. 
I guess I get that they don't want us to be sitting there and hogging tables for that long, but I don't know, just doesn't really make sense to me. Not your typical coffee shop experience I suppose. 
As far as the actual drinks, they're good. I got a matcha green tea with nonfat milk. Can't go wrong with that :)

We had very high expectations for French Press. We seek out the best coffee wherever we go, and heard that they are using Verve beans, had a barista that placed high in a recent competition and are using a top-notch machine. It was very good coffee, but I felt there was more potential than actually realized. The baristas and staff were extremely friendly, and the shop itself had a nice feel with good seating. My cappucino seemed 'small' which is unusual since a cap should always be the same size. It had a good flavor and was well crafted. My wife liked her mocha good enough, but wasn't overly impressed. We'd probably come back here, as it's the best coffee we've found in this area, but overall we felt that they easily have the opportunity to be a 5-star rating. Maybe a little more attention to the espresso shot would take them over the top.

Today, 8/17/21, we tried different items from their menu. He had the Hungry Mans French Toast and I had Josef's Corned Beef Hash. Both were excellent! Hungry Man's French Toast is definitely for a hungry person. 6 pieces of French toast, 2 eggs, bacon and sausage. French toast was delicious, their special recipe. I had Josef's corned beef hash. Special blend of corned beef which was delicious! Definitely not your corned beef in a can. And you get plenty. Plus eggs (your style), potatoes, toast and a mini danish. All scrumptious!  Oh and we had to pick up some of their fabulous pastries on our way out. You know! For snack with coffee later! You definitely need to put "Josef's" on your breakfast/lunch place to go when out and about. Check out their online menu for other options. Oh and if you're a cappuccino or latte lover, ask for theirs. You won't be disappointed!

Went in for brunch with a friend, and loved it!  They have a rather impressive menu for a coffee shop.  Their offer generous, but not outrageous portions, and the food is freshly prepared.  The pesto potatoes are fabulous!  One of the highlights of my breakfast was the lemon curd that accompanied the scone that came with my meal-a fantastic little treat!  I'm not a huge coffee drinker, so I ordered a cafe au lait, which was good, but nothing special.  I am willing to shell out $ for good, freshly prepared food.  My meal came to about $12, which I think is a fair price.

So I will admit that I was late to jump on the Coffeebar bandwagon.  I live in Old Southwest neighborhood, but was so annoyed by all the Coffeebar fanboys (and girls) that I avoided this hipster palace for a long time. I will admit when I am wrong.  I really like the Coffeebar. Atmosphere gets a 5. Especially because of the music. Today they were playing an awesome mix of post-modern alternative (The Specials!). I was so stoked by the music I could hardly focus on work! But I digress... I love Coffeebar because it is in my 'hood and serves good food and coffee.  I personally find the service VERY slow, but if you time it right (2pm after the lunchtime rush) you may find yourself with no wait.  Good seating, free wifi, excellent atmosphere.  So much to like about Coffeebar.  Treat yourself to a coffee and the Giuseppe bar if you want a sweet treat.  It has a perfect mix of chocolate, nutty, crunchy goodness.
Was visiting thanksgiving week. Food and juice was fresh and delicious. It was a nice change from hotel breakfast. The service was very good. Wish I had a place like this near me.

Being 100% fresh off the boat from Vietnam, I didn't expect much from this place at all compared to the authentic dishes in my home country. But come on, we're in SANTA BARBARA guys, so cut these people some slack. The most authentic Pho you can find in the states would be located in California cities of Garden Grove, Westminster, or San Jose. The cooks are Vietnamese, so it made me feel sort of at home when I hear them talk in Vietnamese in the kitchen. I felt pretty alone in Santa Barbara due to the lack of people from Vietnam, until I came here. 
 
Now about the food, it's quite delicious! HUGE drink selection! I definitely recommend the taro, mixed berry, marcha, or banana smoothie! But honestly....all of the smoothies are amazing. If you upgrade to a milkshake it comes with ice cream!! I had the Combination Pho and it was pretty decent! $10 is what's expected in Isla Vista...taking in consideration the owner has to go a long way to get the necessary resources since Santa Barbara literally has no good asian market. The bowl was filling. However, if you want to order a large, go for it! That portion is amazingly generous!!  ***For all you chili lovers, ask for chili paste to go with your soup!!*** trust me it makes a huge difference.
Also, the cups they use for water is so VIETNAMESE it made so happy lol!
The girls working there are super cute haha, but I also wish they hired a waitress who spoke Vietnamese as well (like me )!
I'll be coming back to try the Bun Bo Hue and Bap Xao. Will keep updating this review.
UPDATE: they ran out of Bap Xao but no biggie I tried their Bun Bo Hue and I'd recommend this for everyone! I actually prefer this over their Pho. If you're on a quick run and need a cheap meal to go get their Banh Mi special. They have fresh coconut here to drink right out of the fruit. Very nostalgic :)
I ordered the baked eggs with spinach and sautéed onions. Delicious! So glad I found this place. Breakfast was served quickly. I hope I get to come back while I am in town.

All I have to say is that the oak grilled burgers are another one of my addictions! I am not even a burger girl!  They are sooooooo good!
Then there is the oak grilled artichoke.  Oh my gosh!  With fresh salsa and a secret recipe mayo dip.
I always get happy with the perfectly spicy just enough vodka (a lot), real horseradish Bloody Mary!
Make sure you go for dinner though because lunch can sometimes be a little inconsistent.
Also very reasonable for the quality and great service.  
This is a great place to eat.

My wife was excited to see this is now open and receiving great reviews so we decided to stop in on Sunday morning before running errands. 
The interior is cute and cozy feeling and provides space to sit and enjoy your coffee and pastries. 
We were immediately greeted by two friendly baristas who were helpful and efficient. The white chocolate mocha we ordered was made quickly and my wife said it tasted delicious. 
Happy to see another business in Golden Valley, we will be back!

Went here for the first time today with a friend for late lunch.  We were both  impressed with the food.  I ordered a steak / zoodles dish that was very tasty and had several types of vegetables in it.  Most now know that zoodles is zucchini spirals cut to look like noodles. But, of course, it is zucchini and not to be mistaken for noodles.  The dish was arranged in an attractive way and it was plenty of food.  My friend enjoyed her menu choice which was ground turkey, zoodles and more of mexican food style ingredients.  
I could have given this cafe a 5 star review but decided on 4 stars mostly due to the very casual, counter style ordering / self serve.  But the cafe does have a comfortable feel to it. The menu is creatively developed and it's a large menu for a modest sized establishment.
We noticed there is a good selection of grab and go food when you enter the cafe.  This would be good when out and about -- one could grab lunch or dinner to take home.  I'm sure I'll return to BFF Cafe to dine and/or just pick up something to take home for a meal.

Wonderful brunch option in the Funk Zone. Food is fresh and biscuit sandwiches are made perfectly. I'd recommend Green Eggs and Ham for sure and am planning to go back and try all the baked goods as well. Also, sharing the space w a wine bar is a nice touch ;)

Nothing bad. Nothing too exciting. 
Full stack (3) of buttermilk pancakes for $11 is tough to swallow and they were just ok. 
Chorizo hash was again, just ok, not much to it; eggs, chorizo and potatoes with some black beans and a bit of avocado.   
Water has a strong chlorine taste, could not even drink it. 
Friendly and hard working staff.

No vegan options. Super disappointed because one of my friends just went there a few days ago and they told her that her food was vegan. Went today to check it out and turns out someone lied to her. Not only is it dangerous (people have food allergies) it is also unethical to lie about what you are serving people.

Food was good but not warm. My French toast was cold for some reason. Cute court yard setting but you can hear 3 different musics going on from the restaurant itself and from two other restaurants next to them. It's quite pricey when breakfast items don't service with any side but maybe because they use quality ingredients.

Two Words: Loose-Leaf Tea
This store is very unique. I have to say that their teas have never disappointed me. I think my favorite one is the ambrosia, I love saying it and I love drinking it. Usually, when I order teas in other places, it is quite bland. So, I was actually amazingly surprised that they have a unique blend and a variety of loose leaf teas.
Their staff is friendly, they have consistently given me quality service. 
I have never tried their coffee because I usually go in the afternoon. If I drink coffee then, I will not be able to sleep. 
Their seats are somewhat limited because there is someone reading their daily newspaper, studying, or having a conversation. It is quite full. 
If you do see an empty table, I recommend sitting down and just enjoy your beverage or snack. There is such a warm, cozy feeling to this place. Even during a summer day. There are high chairs, regular tables, and even a comfy sofa. 
I will definitely go more during the wintertime to see if they will use their fireplace.

Used to be one of best options for lunch & dinner around my place .. Sadly ever since it's remodeled, got spacious though food doesn't taste same.. I still tried couple more times though now I know I am not going back soon ..

If you have a lot of time to spare to eat here Then it is worth it.  We always like to go for breakfast.  I have had lunch there a few times when I worked on that side of town but I am a sucker for a tasty breakfast.  We  grab a table and usually it takes a little bit to even be acknowledge by the waitress but if you know that is what to expect then fine.  European dining can be like that, in some places when you go to dinner you could have that table all night.  I think they may follow that mindset.  It can be annoying if you are hungry or you want to get in and out of there quickly.  But I digress back to the food.  They have a pretty good sized breakfast menu that they serve until 3pm.  They even have a few healthy options.  There is usually four of us and this time was no different.  We all usually take a bite off each other's plate as I don't think I have had a dish there I don't like.  We got the green benedict,  Denver omelette, corned beef and hash,  and the crepes with strawberries and French cream.  I have also had the waffles and the scrambles there and those are usually made very well.  The green benedict is one of my favorite things that they serve.  The spinach is creamy and the sauce has the perfect amount of tang to it.  They do a very good poached egg there.  I am not usually a poached or fried egg person because I am not a fan of the yolk but for the green benedict it all works so well I have no problem with eating it.  The Denver omelette has good flavor and has a good ratio of ingredients, ham, peppers, cheese, and onions.  It normally comes with hollandaise sauce on it but you can have it without.  It is also one of the items that can be made heart healthy.  The corned beef is good I like to order it because it is tasty and it fills you up.  I usually get the eggs scrambled and they are always light and fluffy.  The crepes are one of the best things they do there.  These were up to the task.  They had a good strawberry flavor and the cream was airy and smooth.  They had that melt in your mouth quality that just put them over the top.  The potatoes that come with most of the breakfasts are like home fries.  Good but don't eat too much of them because you will fill up quickly.  Some of the dishes on the menu, I think the scrambles and omelettes come with a small danish as well as all of the other things that come on the plate.  It is a nice little surprise  for your meal.  We always get a latte and those are pretty decent and one server makes it better than the others but it isn't bad,  The coffees go well with the breakfast.  When we did lunch my favorite thing to get was the lunch special for that curried chicken salad.  If you have not had it you must get it.  Sometimes I have had soup there that I have to add pepper to to give it an oomph of flavor.  but hey they can't be good at everything.  They do have great pastries I like to order out of the case.  I wouldn't recommend a special order.  It can be pricey and sometimes the job isn't well done.  We have also had them tell us they can't do an order of even a dozen cookies because they don't have the time.  We called a few weeks in advance.  But nonetheless you can just go in and something out of the case and that works just fine.

Vegetarians, rejoice! If you have been driving a great distance and can still see taillights when you close your eyes, and the idea of walking into a blinking, pinging casino is making your consider merging into a highway divide, Cafe Deluxe is here for you. It's a calm, clean space with a variety of vegetarian and vegan options and tasteful decor. I recommend the French toast. It tastes like bananas.

LAZINESS AND DISRESPECT , this was my first thought when I walked into this place.
The manager and the rest of the employees don't care if you bring business there!
To the owners-owner: 
The manager has no knowledge about cross contamination and how the food is prepared!!!
 
You  needs to take a bold decision about management and training!
Money is not an end in itself but just a tool.
Great food for a great price! Every time i have gone in to Bab Cafe the staff is always super helpful and educated on their product and make recommendations. Would 10/10 recommend to anyone!

My girlfriends and I had SUCH an amazing experience at Phamous Cafe today! The service was friendly and attentive. Dan (the manager) is so sweet and knowledgable about the cooking methods and ingredients which was very helpful because our friends is allergic to so many things common in Vietnamese cooking. He was able to make suggestions based on her allergies and she had a great time and loved all of the food! We all enjoyed everything we ordered (the pho (P.2, P.4, P.12) eggrolls, the combination bahn mi, and Thai Iced Tea) so much! Thank you Phamous Cafe! I'll be ordering some food to go on my way back home!

Mongolian beef is amazing! Very large portion. Doesn't come with rice so that's the only downside but the taste compensates. Probably best to order takeout then make your own rice so you can get the best of both worlds

Backyard Bowls is always something I look forward to on a warm Summer morning right before a day at the beach. It's definitely more of a treat rather than a healthy meal, but very filling nonetheless and gives you energy for hours. They are very generous with their fresh fruit, peanut butter, coconut and granola toppings. Some toppings are limited to their seasonal availability. 
I've been coming here for years but generally as a special occasion treat as they are so pricey and full of sugar. I've had everything from the Acai Oatmeal to the Green Bowl. The Hercules is my go-to smoothie here, but again very sugary and not the healthiest protein shake. It's made with hemp milk which gives it the perfect texture and thickness but is often very heavy. My go-to is generally the Dragon Bowl because I love the pitaya kiwi mix. If you want the cheapest, least filling option I'd recommend the Berry Kid's Bowl. That is the only bowl they small in that size. 
This Backyard Bowls is located on lower State St next to Santa Barbara Roasting Company. It has its own 75 min free parking lot and street parking nearby, though i've never seen the lot full. You can park here and walk State St up and down after enjoying a bowl or even head down to the pier. It's a really nice central location, limited seating indoors and out, though. It's generally pretty busy so expect to wait a few minutes for your order to be done. They also have a drink fridge inside with kombuchas, waters and teas to go. Great morning spot to stop at before exploring the main touristy areas of SB.

The service was terrible and my food was cold. The waitresses  were giving me constant attitude when I was being nice. I even spoke with the manager and he also gave me attitude. Never coming back again.

While the chicken tenders were big and meaty and the breading was well made, I wish they had the boneless chicken tenders that the old South Bab x Chicken location had. I also liked the other locations' dipping sauces. :( 
Otherwise, an excellent location and service. Took protocols seriously and were very helpful over the phone!

I really like this Starbucks if I need some "me time". There is plenty of comfortable seats to just sit back and enjoy my coffee while reading my kindle. My coffee is made exactly like I ask. The staff seem to enjoy their job and are friendly without going overboard to where it seems fake . This is one of my favorites. They also have a drive thru

This is the best place to get pretty decent Taiwanese food in Reno, you really can't beat their service and menu.... sure they don't have the quintessential item, stinky tofu but maybe they will get it soon, but other than that, you really can't complain about what they offer the soups are great, the bento boxes are on point, if you want to try really savory Chinese/Taiwanese food get to this place asap.

The worst Mexican I've ever had in my entire life by far and nothing even comes close (I've had some bad food over the years). WHY WOULD YOU EVER PUT PRE-MADE (boxed) MASHED POTATOES IN A BREAKFAST BURRITO? WHY? I thought maybe I'll give their lunch menu a try and not jump to conclusions. Heck maybe it might be better.. I had a "Carne Asada" burrito and it tasted absolutely atrocious. They put a can of refried beans that weren't even heated all the way. They used burnt niblets of mystery meat to maybe "save" money and cut corners. I would say Chipotle is more authentic than this place but even that's giving them too much credit. Taco Bell is a better comparison with the slight edge to TBL. DO NOT GO HERE, but hey at least your meal comes with a few free chips.

The chick that works here is seriously retarded. Spacey as fck, dosent pay attention, and can't take an order. 
Its IV, so can't expect much. 
The pho was a little funky... wanst a huge fan of the broth, but it had a lot of veggies and tofu in it, so i was fairly satisfied. 
Iced coffee was good. 
meh.

Great tasting food but so expensive especially since they downsized their meal quantity. The last times the beef and broccoli was in round, red bowl, but now it's in a small regular Chinese style container. Disappointing.. $20 for just that.

I love this place!!
It's atmosphere is eclectic: soothing and energizing at the same time. Plus, their menu provides an array of options for the all levels of coffee connoisseurs that come from locally-provided ingredients and well-treated farm animals. I enjoyed two of their mocha cappuccinos and their frittatas. The cappuccinos were beautiful, warming, and delicious. The frittatas were a little dry, but still satisfying. I recommend this place as a meeting place for a light brunch, to catch up with friends, or to entrench yourself in your recent favorite read, but prepared to be there for a couple hours. You'll get sucked into this comforting and inviting abode.

Edit: I bumped up my review to four starts because after I was unhappy they took off my tax (4.95). But then I put it back down to two when I found out that the kids meal was actually nine dollars because they gave us a three dollar up charge for changing the fries to fruit. They also did this to my mother-in-law. So we paid nine dollars for that kids meal....
Mixed feelings. The Wienerschnitzel is good but I wouldn't order anything else because the portions are just ridiculously small (besides the Wienerschnitzel) it was $6 for my daughters kids-meal. We ordered her a grilled cheese. They literally served her half of a grilled cheese that was cooked on really small bread so really it was more like half of a half of a grilled cheese.... not really willing to help you if you're unhappy. I really enjoy the atmosphere and getting coffee here so I'm very conflicted. Good pastries. The kids meal was not enough for my two-year-old, I couldn't imagine bringing my five-year-old here and ordering that.

Healthy but hardy, great portion sizes, and a versatile menu. The restaurant doesn't have the most amount of decor, ambiance, service..... but it's solid food, consistent, something for everyone. A go- to for easy, healthy food in downtown Santa Barbara.

Alrighty, I have been to Cafe DeLuxe multiple times and cannot believe that I have some how left out their review! Sorry man!

I must begin by saying that I love Cafe DeLuxe for multiple reasons. First, it is a great place to work. They have free wi-fi and I can sit either outside if it is nice or inside the adorable restaurant. 

Second, I love how fresh all the products are they use for their food and how they have some many healthy options! It just makes the food taste that much better. The variety is awesome! I have had multiple meals at Cafe DeLuxe and think the frittata with its potato crust and the homefries are amazing! Definitely a must try if you are going for the first time. The home made chai and smoothies are also good choices to check out!

My husband also really enjoys Cafe DeLuxe which makes it a great place to bring the family. As I mentioned previously they have wi-fi which makes it a popular place for me and my colleagues to be able to get some work done while having some great food. Some of our best work has came out of that place!

Keep up the amazing establishment you have going Cafe DeLuxe!

Had the basil chicken... scary as hell. I'm not sure if it's Taiwanese style to fragment chicken bones into dozens of deadly shards or what, but geeze someone needs to take the cleavers away from chef-showboat back there. Why you chop my food sooo much, bro? U mad? I've eaten food from many cultures in many countries but never anything as scary as that. When you try to kill me off with chicken bones like some kind of voodoo shaman I will fight back with Taiwanese stars (removal) :)  
Really though, aside from the chicken being deadly sharp, it had great flavor. I'm sure the other less-deadly dishes are tasty as well. Also, the boba was great and while we were there more than a few people seemed to be coming in just for that.

The toppings for the frozen yogurt were all stale and old. Many of the sweeter toppings had been in the machines for so long that they were all stuck together and nothing would even come out. All the gummy toppings were hard as rocks and it was generally a very unpleasant eating experience. If I were to go again, I would stick to chocolates and nuts. But I doubt that will happen. The kids working there were not very personable. The only thing they said to us the whole time was the price of our frozen yogurt when we finally went up to purchase them.

EDIT: Sorry I was trying to be nice. For the sake of clarity I'll say that I think the place is disgusting and the employees are rude.

Please stop with the lavender scones they taste like perfume. 


Coffee bar is super hip and the hot spot to be. We get it. But their lattes are not so hot. I have had about 10, and every single time they are soooo bitter. The espresso shots are awful. Why have I had about 10 of their lattes if they are so awful?? Cause their pastries are amazing. As is their quinoa bowl. So I come back. All the time. And I convince myself that maybe this time the espresso won't taste like tire grease running down a butt crack luge. If it does I can always wash it down with a delicious macaroon.

Swill is a great place to meet friends or hang out if  you're looking for a coffeehouse with great ambience. There's plenty of seating in a variety of styles- high tops, big tables, sofas or tables outside too. Everyone that I've met there has been really welcoming including the baristas and the owner. 

The large side room is available for rent for private parties, while individual tables can also reserved ahead of time as long as everyone makes a food or drink purchase. 

I'm so glad there is still a coffeehouse in Reno that's nice and comfortable to hangout at!
